1
00:00:00,805 --> 00:00:03,805
(There's no stepping back or giving up.)

2
00:00:04,575 --> 00:00:07,575
(Odd man out DinDin versus Mouse Hunters)

3
00:00:08,275 --> 00:00:11,945
(The first to reach the final destination wins.)

4
00:00:13,085 --> 00:00:15,114
(DinDin is ahead.)

5
00:00:15,115 --> 00:00:16,154
He's off already.

6
00:00:16,155 --> 00:00:19,014
(The Mouse Hunters give chase.)

7
00:00:19,015 --> 00:00:20,884
(Blue, blue, red, yellow, black, purple, yellow)

8
00:00:20,885 --> 00:00:24,325
(The final destination is a rough journey away.)

9
00:00:25,825 --> 00:00:29,895
(Chase or be chased)

10
00:00:30,735 --> 00:00:33,205
(The mouse! Let's get it!)

11
00:00:34,105 --> 00:00:37,575
(After a breathtaking race...)

12
00:00:38,575 --> 00:00:40,545
(Mouse DinDin wins.)

13
00:00:41,245 --> 00:00:42,915
(The competition is not yet over.)

14
00:00:43,715 --> 00:00:45,475
(Now it's psychological.)

15
00:00:45,575 --> 00:00:46,645
My knees hurt.

16
00:00:47,315 --> 00:00:50,084
(The hunters must act to deceive Mouse DinDin.)

17
00:00:50,085 --> 00:00:51,415
It's Seon Ho. Number four.

18
00:00:51,515 --> 00:00:53,155
(Mouse DinDin is correct twice in a row.)

19
00:00:53,885 --> 00:00:55,185
(The hunters lose control.)

20
00:00:55,285 --> 00:00:56,494
Come here!

21
00:00:56,495 --> 00:00:58,054
(Current score of You're the Fake One)

22
00:00:58,055 --> 00:00:59,765
(DinDin 2, Mouse Hunters 1)

23
00:01:00,465 --> 00:01:04,265
(2 Days 1 Night)

24
00:01:04,935 --> 00:01:07,865
This is the final round.

25
00:01:09,105 --> 00:01:10,575
How can we catch the mouse?

26
00:01:11,005 --> 00:01:12,204
Let's set a trap.

27
00:01:12,205 --> 00:01:13,575
In this last round,

28
00:01:13,905 --> 00:01:15,304
you must identify the one person...

29
00:01:15,305 --> 00:01:16,945
who didn't run at full speed.

30
00:01:17,045 --> 00:01:18,045
There's more guessing?

31
00:01:18,046 --> 00:01:19,915
Aren't we just entertaining DinDin?

32
00:01:19,985 --> 00:01:21,344
Are we running a playground?

33
00:01:21,345 --> 00:01:23,854
- He just sits still to watch.
- He's having all the fun!

34
00:01:23,855 --> 00:01:24,984
We do all the work!

35
00:01:24,985 --> 00:01:26,424
What are we? We did this...

36
00:01:26,425 --> 00:01:27,525
- and ate.
- Wait.

37
00:01:27,655 --> 00:01:29,995
What do you mean? We run at full speed and he watches?

38
00:01:30,295 --> 00:01:31,424
(Yes.)

39
00:01:31,425 --> 00:01:34,495
Do you see the flag 50m away?

40
00:01:34,825 --> 00:01:35,825
Yes.

41
00:01:35,826 --> 00:01:40,004
Three of you will run up to that flag and back,

42
00:01:40,005 --> 00:01:42,235
so you'll run a total of 100m.

43
00:01:42,535 --> 00:01:44,275
One person will just stand still.

44
00:01:44,475 --> 00:01:46,605
DinDin has to guess...

45
00:01:46,805 --> 00:01:48,445
which one of you didn't run.

46
00:01:48,705 --> 00:01:50,715
Someone has to pretend to be out of breath.

47
00:01:51,015 --> 00:01:52,815
- You must be having fun.
- Me?

48
00:01:53,345 --> 00:01:54,584
It's the best day ever.

49
00:01:54,585 --> 00:01:55,814
(Laughing)

50
00:01:55,815 --> 00:01:57,495
Of all the 2 Days 1 Night episodes I shot,

51
00:01:57,555 --> 00:01:59,585
this has to be one of the top three most fun ones.

52
00:01:59,755 --> 00:02:02,355
It must be fun for him. We fool around and he guesses.

53
00:02:02,585 --> 00:02:04,454
The rest of you will get a chance one day.

54
00:02:04,455 --> 00:02:05,695
I really hope so.

55
00:02:05,855 --> 00:02:08,365
(Time out to strategize)

56
00:02:08,725 --> 00:02:10,535
- How should we act?
- Act tired.

57
00:02:11,135 --> 00:02:12,395
See how this looks.

58
00:02:13,165 --> 00:02:16,935
(Imitating DinDin's front teeth)

59
00:02:17,235 --> 00:02:18,875
Are you trying to be funny or what?

60
00:02:19,605 --> 00:02:21,005
- Hey.
- How's that?

61
00:02:22,005 --> 00:02:23,444
(They're not strategizing.)

62
00:02:23,445 --> 00:02:25,245
(No wonder they can't win.)

63
00:02:25,745 --> 00:02:26,785
We're ready!

64
00:02:27,445 --> 00:02:28,885
Okay. Let's do this.

65
00:02:29,245 --> 00:02:30,485
On your marks!

66
00:02:31,185 --> 00:02:33,455
(3 people set off running.)

67
00:02:34,055 --> 00:02:36,555
(1 is standing still, not running.)

68
00:02:36,795 --> 00:02:37,825
They're fast.

69
00:02:39,725 --> 00:02:42,165
(Who is the one standing behind DinDin?)

70
00:02:42,995 --> 00:02:44,064
That's enough.

71
00:02:44,065 --> 00:02:45,465
(All he hears is ragged breathing.)

72
00:02:45,535 --> 00:02:47,665
Five, four, three,

73
00:02:48,165 --> 00:02:50,235
two, one, turn around!

74
00:02:51,235 --> 00:02:52,305
Save me...

75
00:02:55,305 --> 00:02:56,374
Save me...

76
00:02:56,375 --> 00:02:58,175
(He can't help but laugh.)

77
00:02:58,645 --> 00:02:59,814
(Is fussy Jong Min the one who didn't run?)

78
00:02:59,815 --> 00:03:01,385
My tummy hurts.

79
00:03:01,845 --> 00:03:03,454
(DinDin's options)

80
00:03:03,455 --> 00:03:04,984
(Se Yoon imitating DinDin's front teeth?)

81
00:03:04,985 --> 00:03:06,725
(Joon trying to get his breath back?)

82
00:03:07,685 --> 00:03:10,525
(Or is it Seon Ho who seems relatively okay?)

83
00:03:11,055 --> 00:03:12,595
(He observes them intently.)

84
00:03:12,755 --> 00:03:13,924
My lungs are about to burst.

85
00:03:13,925 --> 00:03:15,224
(Groaning)

86
00:03:15,225 --> 00:03:16,594
- Oh, my throat hurts.
- Hey, hold on.

87
00:03:16,595 --> 00:03:18,635
Guys, step back. Stand behind the line.

88
00:03:18,935 --> 00:03:20,535
- At this rate...
- Gosh, my head hurts.

89
00:03:20,665 --> 00:03:21,734
This won't be easy.

90
00:03:21,735 --> 00:03:22,895
(This isn't an easy mission.)

91
00:03:22,935 --> 00:03:24,135
Seon Ho ran.

92
00:03:24,805 --> 00:03:25,805
What's your reason?

93
00:03:25,806 --> 00:03:27,875
Seon Ho and I have gone for a run a few times.

94
00:03:28,205 --> 00:03:29,914
He has this distinctive look after he runs.

95
00:03:29,915 --> 00:03:32,915
His eyes and nose get big like this. That's his thing.

96
00:03:33,085 --> 00:03:34,215
Oh, this?

97
00:03:34,745 --> 00:03:38,585
(Is it the facial expression he makes after running?)

98
00:03:39,085 --> 00:03:40,324
- What? Is this it?
- Hey.

99
00:03:40,325 --> 00:03:41,625
They got super big.

100
00:03:41,685 --> 00:03:43,805
Based on that, I'm betting that Seon Ho actually ran.

101
00:03:44,125 --> 00:03:46,255
I'm getting the vibe that Se Yoon also ran...

102
00:03:46,595 --> 00:03:49,025
- because I heard heavy footsteps.
- Okay.

103
00:03:49,395 --> 00:03:51,095
They weren't light footsteps.

104
00:03:51,235 --> 00:03:53,605
The footsteps sounded very heavy in the beginning.

105
00:03:53,935 --> 00:03:54,935
(Thud)

106
00:03:54,936 --> 00:03:57,775
(Is that the sound of Se Yoon's running?)

107
00:03:57,905 --> 00:04:00,105
It's between Jong Min and Joon.

108
00:04:01,305 --> 00:04:02,505
- My answer is...
- Okay.

109
00:04:02,945 --> 00:04:04,075
Joon.

110
00:04:04,275 --> 00:04:05,344
What's your reason?

111
00:04:05,345 --> 00:04:08,315
Here's what Joon said at the opening segment.

112
00:04:09,215 --> 00:04:11,785
He mentioned that he had pulled his hamstrings...

113
00:04:12,085 --> 00:04:14,366
because he worked so hard for the cheerleading challenge.

114
00:04:14,785 --> 00:04:17,795
Well, it happened only two days ago.

115
00:04:18,055 --> 00:04:20,164
I strained my ligament, so I stayed in bed yesterday.

116
00:04:20,165 --> 00:04:21,325
Because you danced so hard?

117
00:04:21,395 --> 00:04:23,634
It was odd. I woke up the next day after the challenge.

118
00:04:23,635 --> 00:04:24,864
And I couldn't move my body.

119
00:04:24,865 --> 00:04:27,265
(DinDin remembered that.)

120
00:04:28,135 --> 00:04:30,405
So my answer is...

121
00:04:30,935 --> 00:04:32,005
Joon!

122
00:04:32,535 --> 00:04:33,575
Joon.

123
00:04:33,845 --> 00:04:37,275
All right. The four of you will stand behind the line.

124
00:04:37,815 --> 00:04:39,244
The member who didn't run...

125
00:04:39,245 --> 00:04:41,715
will take a step forward and reveal the answer.

126
00:04:42,215 --> 00:04:43,885
What's the answer?

127
00:04:44,515 --> 00:04:45,985
All right. We'll reveal it.

128
00:04:46,425 --> 00:04:48,585
One, two, three.

129
00:04:49,185 --> 00:04:50,424
- You're not going to change?
- I won't.

130
00:04:50,425 --> 00:04:51,655
Seon Ho, step back.

131
00:04:52,225 --> 00:04:53,425
Go ahead. Step forward.

132
00:04:53,825 --> 00:04:58,195
(Joon was the one who didn't run.)

133
00:04:58,695 --> 00:05:01,905
(But Joon did push-ups, so he could pretend to be out of breath.)

134
00:05:02,265 --> 00:05:04,134
- Here's why.
- I have such a good memory.

135
00:05:04,135 --> 00:05:05,374
Seon Ho suddenly said this.

136
00:05:05,375 --> 00:05:06,904
"Guys, Joon strained his muscles."

137
00:05:06,905 --> 00:05:07,905
Yes, it was the hamstrings.

138
00:05:07,906 --> 00:05:08,944
- He mentioned that earlier today.
- Really?

139
00:05:08,945 --> 00:05:10,465
- I said that during the shoot?
- Yes.

140
00:05:11,015 --> 00:05:13,584
(He even forgot that he had mentioned it.)

141
00:05:13,585 --> 00:05:17,415
All right. Round Four goes to Team DinDin.

142
00:05:17,755 --> 00:05:18,814
Okay. Draw the cards.

143
00:05:18,815 --> 00:05:20,895
- Should we go to the other side?
- Yes, you should.

144
00:05:21,055 --> 00:05:22,125
- Okay.
- Let me see.

145
00:05:23,025 --> 00:05:24,025
Finally.

146
00:05:24,026 --> 00:05:25,131
(DinDin finally obtains scissors.)

147
00:05:25,155 --> 00:05:26,664
- We got all the cards, right?
- Yes.

148
00:05:26,665 --> 00:05:27,905
- We do have every card.
- Yes.

149
00:05:27,965 --> 00:05:29,834
Let's head to the base camp now.

150
00:05:29,835 --> 00:05:31,064
- Yes!
- Let's go.

151
00:05:31,065 --> 00:05:32,825
(Rock-Paper-Scissors Card Collection Status)

152
00:05:33,965 --> 00:05:36,285
How is it possible that he's beating us one after another?

153
00:05:37,075 --> 00:05:38,205
How can we be this bad?

154
00:05:38,505 --> 00:05:40,305
Guys, it's not over yet.

155
00:05:40,545 --> 00:05:41,605
Right.

156
00:05:42,045 --> 00:05:43,744
- We must play rock-paper-scissors.
- Yes.

157
00:05:43,745 --> 00:05:45,975
So listen up. You haven't lost yet.

158
00:05:46,415 --> 00:05:48,985
He only obtained the rock-paper-scissors cards.

159
00:05:49,185 --> 00:05:51,414
Rock-paper-scissors will determine the real winners.

160
00:05:51,415 --> 00:05:52,415
- Sir.
- Yes?

161
00:05:52,416 --> 00:05:54,954
You keep trying to encourage us under the assumption...

162
00:05:54,955 --> 00:05:56,525
that we lost.

163
00:05:56,655 --> 00:05:59,224
But none of us admitted that we lost to him.

164
00:05:59,225 --> 00:06:00,565
- Well...
- Sir.

165
00:06:00,725 --> 00:06:02,594
You have to stay neutral.

166
00:06:02,595 --> 00:06:04,741
- Okay. You're right.
- You can't keep leaning toward him.

167
00:06:04,765 --> 00:06:06,434
What makes our show exciting?

168
00:06:06,435 --> 00:06:07,804
- A comeback win.
- A comeback win.

169
00:06:07,805 --> 00:06:10,274
A turnaround. With a great turnaround,

170
00:06:10,275 --> 00:06:11,804
- we can dodge penalties.
- Right.

171
00:06:11,805 --> 00:06:13,645
Outcomes like this make our show entertaining.

172
00:06:13,945 --> 00:06:16,105
Honestly, I didn't use my brain once today on purpose.

173
00:06:16,375 --> 00:06:17,644
- Really?
- I didn't want to.

174
00:06:17,645 --> 00:06:19,325
- Really?
- No games required me to think.

175
00:06:19,515 --> 00:06:22,045
(He only used his head to lift the bucket today.)

176
00:06:22,645 --> 00:06:23,885
I'll start using my brain now.

177
00:06:24,385 --> 00:06:26,065
Did you say the losing team had a penalty?

178
00:06:26,115 --> 00:06:29,325
There's a big penalty that's perfect for Yanggu.

179
00:06:29,625 --> 00:06:30,725
A big penalty?

180
00:06:31,395 --> 00:06:32,795
- I bet it's hiking.
- It's hiking.

181
00:06:33,365 --> 00:06:35,085
I don't think it's hiking. We're in Yanggu.

182
00:06:35,395 --> 00:06:36,665
Will we enlist or something?

183
00:06:37,435 --> 00:06:38,664
As a military cook.

184
00:06:38,665 --> 00:06:40,035
(As a military cook!)

185
00:06:40,565 --> 00:06:42,565
Guys, this is our base camp.

186
00:06:43,475 --> 00:06:44,675
It's a school.

187
00:06:44,735 --> 00:06:47,675
This used to be a branch school.

188
00:06:48,105 --> 00:06:51,275
The former branch school is our base camp for the night.

189
00:06:52,215 --> 00:06:53,715
- This is nice.
- Oh, this is nice.

190
00:06:53,885 --> 00:06:55,184
- The school field is big too.
- Yes.

191
00:06:55,185 --> 00:06:56,245
- Let's do it.
- Go.

192
00:06:56,385 --> 00:06:58,485
- Catch the mouse, squeak, squeak.
- Squeak

193
00:06:59,355 --> 00:07:00,515
- What's going on?
- My gosh.

194
00:07:00,625 --> 00:07:02,785
- This looks legit.
- They really went all out for it.

195
00:07:03,085 --> 00:07:04,754
Did they have to do this just for rock-paper-scissors?

196
00:07:04,755 --> 00:07:06,995
(Did they have to do this just for rock-paper-scissors?)

197
00:07:09,195 --> 00:07:12,395
(4-on-1 Rock-Paper-Scissors Battle)

198
00:07:12,695 --> 00:07:14,435
This is how we'll play rock-paper-scissors?

199
00:07:15,005 --> 00:07:16,464
- No, this looks about right.
- Seriously?

200
00:07:16,465 --> 00:07:17,734
(The game of rock-paper-scissors will decide the final results.)

201
00:07:17,735 --> 00:07:19,104
- This is no joke.
- There's a notebook.

202
00:07:19,105 --> 00:07:20,474
- We must consider possibilities.
- Hold on.

203
00:07:20,475 --> 00:07:23,414
Do you think they belong at the same table as me?

204
00:07:23,415 --> 00:07:25,415
(The fact that they're at the same table as me...)

205
00:07:25,975 --> 00:07:27,735
If you feel uncomfortable, sit on the floor.

206
00:07:28,515 --> 00:07:30,714
All right, guys. You all have the rock-paper-scissors cards...

207
00:07:30,715 --> 00:07:31,715
you obtained, right?

208
00:07:31,715 --> 00:07:32,715
- Yes.
- Yes.

209
00:07:32,955 --> 00:07:34,085
These cards...

210
00:07:34,925 --> 00:07:37,595
will decide who gets to eat dinner tonight.

211
00:07:37,995 --> 00:07:39,864
- I knew it.
- If we lose this one too,

212
00:07:39,865 --> 00:07:41,194
- It will be the worst.
- it will be the worst.

213
00:07:41,195 --> 00:07:43,395
- I'm starving. That's right.
- Then we have a problem.

214
00:07:43,635 --> 00:07:45,534
Yanggu in Gangwon Province sits at a high altitude.

215
00:07:45,535 --> 00:07:47,335
So Yanggu is the top producer of gomchwi...

216
00:07:47,405 --> 00:07:49,605
which is known for its excellent aroma and texture.

217
00:07:49,765 --> 00:07:51,134
- Gomchwi.
- Gomchwi is so good.

218
00:07:51,135 --> 00:07:52,635
Gomchwi is great for wraps.

219
00:07:52,905 --> 00:07:54,944
And Yanggu produces the finest dried radish greens.

220
00:07:54,945 --> 00:07:56,404
- Right. Yanggu is famous for it.
- Yes.

221
00:07:56,405 --> 00:07:59,515
Let me share the menu for tonight's dinner now.

222
00:08:00,115 --> 00:08:02,515
It will include gopchang hot pot with dried radish greens...

223
00:08:02,585 --> 00:08:04,314
- It's really good.
- and beef doenjang paste.

224
00:08:04,315 --> 00:08:05,685
(Beef doenjang paste)

225
00:08:05,915 --> 00:08:07,955
The meal also includes seasoned squid with vinegar,

226
00:08:08,485 --> 00:08:10,095
fresh gomchwi, deep-fried gomchwi,

227
00:08:10,525 --> 00:08:12,365
- That's good.
- dried radish green dumplings,

228
00:08:12,395 --> 00:08:14,794
- and gomchwi tofu jeon.
- Nice.

229
00:08:14,795 --> 00:08:15,964
You'll get all of these dishes.

230
00:08:15,965 --> 00:08:17,525
- No way.
- It will be a generous meal.

231
00:08:18,665 --> 00:08:20,265
How did you know I love jeon?

232
00:08:21,105 --> 00:08:22,204
- All right.
- That's crazy.

233
00:08:22,205 --> 00:08:23,274
We can totally beat him.

234
00:08:23,275 --> 00:08:25,405
All right. You will now play rock-paper-scissors...

235
00:08:25,535 --> 00:08:27,505
for a meal made with local ingredients.

236
00:08:28,045 --> 00:08:30,375
You'll play a best-of-five game.

237
00:08:30,545 --> 00:08:33,685
The team with more wins will get to eat dinner.

238
00:08:34,215 --> 00:08:35,344
- For your information, - Okay.

239
00:08:35,345 --> 00:08:37,384
Once you play a card,

240
00:08:37,385 --> 00:08:39,154
- it will be discarded.
- Right.

241
00:08:39,155 --> 00:08:40,725
It can't be used again.

242
00:08:40,885 --> 00:08:42,584
So the goal is to win three rounds first, right?

243
00:08:42,585 --> 00:08:43,624
That's right.

244
00:08:43,625 --> 00:08:44,894
How do you want this to go?

245
00:08:44,895 --> 00:08:46,094
- What?
- Should I let you win two rounds...

246
00:08:46,095 --> 00:08:47,995
- and beat you the rest?
- What do you mean?

247
00:08:48,165 --> 00:08:50,294
Should I let you win two rounds and beat you the rest?

248
00:08:50,295 --> 00:08:52,034
So it will be a comeback win for me.

249
00:08:52,035 --> 00:08:53,835
Or should I let it play out naturally?

250
00:08:54,235 --> 00:08:55,664
- Let it play out naturally.
- Let it play out?

251
00:08:55,665 --> 00:08:57,335
- Let it play out.
- Okay.

252
00:08:57,805 --> 00:08:59,874
(The idiots are offended.)

253
00:08:59,875 --> 00:09:01,604
- Right.
- We counted all the possibilities.

254
00:09:01,605 --> 00:09:02,605
(Their pride is at stake.)

255
00:09:02,606 --> 00:09:03,744
Let's give it some suspense.

256
00:09:03,745 --> 00:09:05,645
I'm holding these cards.

