DinDin has two rock cards now.

508
00:17:39,095 --> 00:17:42,895
And he still has three paper cards.

509
00:17:43,165 --> 00:17:44,264
Gosh, what a bummer.

510
00:17:44,265 --> 00:17:46,935
Mouse Hunters had a lot of scissors cards.

511
00:17:47,065 --> 00:17:49,134
When they played scissors, they lost the round.

512
00:17:49,135 --> 00:17:52,835
They now have 2 scissors cards and 1 paper card.

513
00:17:53,205 --> 00:17:55,374
All right. They're quickly crunching the data.

514
00:17:55,375 --> 00:17:58,175
Will it be the paper card or the scissors card?

515
00:17:58,815 --> 00:18:01,144
- So given the nature of the game, - It's not so bad.

516
00:18:01,145 --> 00:18:02,544
- psychologically-speaking, - It's not so bad.

517
00:18:02,545 --> 00:18:03,684
We can relax a bit.

518
00:18:03,685 --> 00:18:05,984
Mouse Hunters have one win under their belt.

519
00:18:05,985 --> 00:18:08,454
- He said we didn't have the guts.
- The fact that...

520
00:18:08,455 --> 00:18:10,254
- it didn't end in three rounds...
- Right. That crossed my mind too.

521
00:18:10,255 --> 00:18:13,025
Would surprise the viewers.

522
00:18:13,325 --> 00:18:14,424
What should we do now?

523
00:18:14,425 --> 00:18:16,525
- Then...
- Let's lower our voices now.

524
00:18:17,495 --> 00:18:19,615
(Will Jong Min show off his intelligence once again?)

525
00:18:19,865 --> 00:18:22,405
(Listening intently)

526
00:18:25,235 --> 00:18:26,305
What do you want to do?

527
00:18:28,275 --> 00:18:29,374
(You can say that out loud.)

528
00:18:29,375 --> 00:18:30,405
- All right.
- Seriously.

529
00:18:30,575 --> 00:18:32,574
Mouse DinDin is finally pondering about his move.

530
00:18:32,575 --> 00:18:33,645
It's not bad.

531
00:18:33,885 --> 00:18:35,444
This round is really important.

532
00:18:35,445 --> 00:18:36,884
This round will be a critical one.

533
00:18:36,885 --> 00:18:39,085
Seon Ho, what do you think?

534
00:18:39,215 --> 00:18:40,384
- Draw it here.
- Draw it.

535
00:18:40,385 --> 00:18:41,385
- Gosh, I...
- Share your opinion.

536
00:18:41,386 --> 00:18:42,424
- What do you think?
- So...

537
00:18:42,425 --> 00:18:43,654
Let's think about it. Hold on.

538
00:18:43,655 --> 00:18:45,024
(They will write to each other starting now.)

539
00:18:45,025 --> 00:18:47,695
Here's what I think.

540
00:18:48,525 --> 00:18:49,694
(Gutsy)

541
00:18:49,695 --> 00:18:52,094
- This is the only reason.
- I see.

542
00:18:52,095 --> 00:18:53,095
- That's why?
- I... Yes.

543
00:18:53,096 --> 00:18:55,035
- I agree. So...
- Yes.

544
00:18:55,235 --> 00:18:57,534
(Mouse Hunters' cards)

545
00:18:57,535 --> 00:18:59,735
Everyone, I'm getting sleepy. I'll give you 30 seconds.

546
00:19:01,305 --> 00:19:02,574
Here's what I think.

547
00:19:02,575 --> 00:19:05,075
I think we can take a risk in the last round.

548
00:19:05,445 --> 00:19:06,515
All right.

549
00:19:06,615 --> 00:19:07,645
- I...
- Let me explain.

550
00:19:07,845 --> 00:19:10,114
Let's say we both play paper and we get a tie.

551
00:19:10,115 --> 00:19:12,155
- Then he'll win.
- He'll win by playing rock next.

552
00:19:12,915 --> 00:19:14,084
Let's go with this.

553
00:19:14,085 --> 00:19:15,725
- I'll give you five seconds. Five, - No.

554
00:19:15,955 --> 00:19:17,794
- four...
- It's only rock-paper-scissors.

555
00:19:17,795 --> 00:19:20,155
Why are we getting so nervous?

556
00:19:20,295 --> 00:19:21,894
I really have no idea what to play.

557
00:19:21,895 --> 00:19:24,055
- All right. Pick your card.
- It's piercing my heart.

558
00:19:24,295 --> 00:19:25,665
I'll give you 20 seconds.

559
00:19:25,865 --> 00:19:27,094
- Why do I keep...
- Pick your card.

560
00:19:27,095 --> 00:19:28,435
Thinking they're smart?

561
00:19:28,605 --> 00:19:29,634
This is driving me crazy.

562
00:19:29,635 --> 00:19:30,704
- He's playing mind games.
- That's a mind game.

563
00:19:30,705 --> 00:19:32,405
He must be nervous right now.

564
00:19:32,805 --> 00:19:34,851
- If so, we should play this card.
- Which card did you want to play?

565
00:19:34,875 --> 00:19:36,704
I wanted to play this card.

566
00:19:36,705 --> 00:19:38,721
- I picked the same card.
- What about you, Jong Min?

567
00:19:38,745 --> 00:19:39,974
Jong Min wanted to play scissors.

568
00:19:39,975 --> 00:19:42,715
(Speaking it out loud)

569
00:19:43,145 --> 00:19:44,614
I was going to play scissors. You...

570
00:19:44,615 --> 00:19:46,384
(Did he accidentally reveal their real strategy?)

571
00:19:46,385 --> 00:19:47,485
I won't listen to that.

572
00:19:48,085 --> 00:19:49,184
Let's think about it again.

573
00:19:49,185 --> 00:19:50,795
- Let's start again.
- All right.

574
00:19:50,925 --> 00:19:52,494
- Give us 1 more minute.
- Give us 1 more minute. Wait.

575
00:19:52,495 --> 00:19:53,625
He revealed our play.

576
00:19:54,365 --> 00:19:55,724
Joon revealed it.

577
00:19:55,725 --> 00:19:56,894
- Let's come up with another plan.
- Gosh.

578
00:19:56,895 --> 00:19:58,764
- Let's start over. Just one minute.
- Another plan.

579
00:19:58,765 --> 00:20:00,341
- What should we do now?
- Let's start over.

580
00:20:00,365 --> 00:20:02,341
- Are you ready, Mouse Hunters?
- What do you think?

581
00:20:02,365 --> 00:20:03,435
Pick your card.

582
00:20:04,105 --> 00:20:05,634
I think you're a smart bunch.

583
00:20:05,635 --> 00:20:06,935
- You think we're smart?
- Yes.

584
00:20:07,105 --> 00:20:08,774
- All right.
- Wait. I want to play this.

585
00:20:08,775 --> 00:20:10,174
- No. I...
- I want to play this card.

586
00:20:10,175 --> 00:20:11,644
- I won't change my card.
- I'll go with this.

587
00:20:11,645 --> 00:20:13,445
- He won't change his card.
- What about you?

588
00:20:14,445 --> 00:20:15,814
Let's go with this card.

589
00:20:15,815 --> 00:20:17,455
- I'll give you five seconds. Five, - No.

590
00:20:17,485 --> 00:20:18,514
Four...

591
00:20:18,515 --> 00:20:21,225
- That's why I think...
- We should change our card?

592
00:20:21,325 --> 00:20:22,924
We should listen to Joon.

593
00:20:22,925 --> 00:20:24,171
How many times are we changing our mind?

594
00:20:24,195 --> 00:20:26,325
- Here's why. I was bluffing him.
- Five,

595
00:20:26,795 --> 00:20:28,324
- four, - So we're going with this?

596
00:20:28,325 --> 00:20:29,425
- Yes.
- three...

597
00:20:30,395 --> 00:20:33,094
(Right after Round 3 began...)

598
00:20:33,095 --> 00:20:34,564
All right. Let's check.

599
00:20:34,565 --> 00:20:36,004
(Whispering)

600
00:20:36,005 --> 00:20:37,164
(I think...)

601
00:20:37,165 --> 00:20:39,004
(I think we can take a risk in the last round.)

602
00:20:39,005 --> 00:20:40,875
(Speaking out loud)

603
00:20:41,975 --> 00:20:46,015
(He said it out loud, so DinDin could hear it.)

604
00:20:46,975 --> 00:20:49,815
(Speaking out loud again)

605
00:20:50,445 --> 00:20:53,055
(Joon helped Jong Min bluff.)

606
00:20:53,415 --> 00:20:55,685
(After hinting that they'd play scissors, )

607
00:20:56,455 --> 00:20:58,725
(when DinDin played his card...)

608
00:20:59,625 --> 00:21:01,225
I think you're a smart bunch.

609
00:21:02,065 --> 00:21:04,635
(they changed it to the paper card.)

610
00:21:04,865 --> 00:21:06,235
I was bluffing him.

611
00:21:06,535 --> 00:21:08,204
- Four, - So we're going with this?

612
00:21:08,205 --> 00:21:09,905
- Yes.
- three... One. Play your card.

613
00:21:10,635 --> 00:21:12,275
I kept giving him hints on purpose.

614
00:21:13,175 --> 00:21:14,244
- Whoever loses this round...
- Let's flip it.

615
00:21:14,245 --> 00:21:15,245
Will lose the game.

616
00:21:15,445 --> 00:21:16,504
Let's flip it.

617
00:21:16,505 --> 00:21:17,751
Whoever loses this round will lose the game.

618
00:21:17,775 --> 00:21:18,975
Here it goes. All right.

619
00:21:19,615 --> 00:21:21,744
Let's say rock-paper-scissors together.

620
00:21:21,745 --> 00:21:23,721
(Mouse Hunters pretended that they'd play scissors.)

621
00:21:23,745 --> 00:21:25,754
Let's see if he'll play the card they want.

622
00:21:25,755 --> 00:21:27,995
Will it end in disappointment? Or will there be a twist?

623
00:21:30,055 --> 00:21:32,425
Flip the card when I say rock-paper-scissors.

624
00:21:32,668 --> 00:21:35,167
Rock-paper-scissors!

625
00:21:35,168 --> 00:21:36,438
(What's the result?)

626
00:21:37,178 --> 00:21:39,578
(Mouse Hunters played paper after hinting it'd be scissors.)

627
00:21:40,648 --> 00:21:42,518
(Rock)

628
00:21:42,778 --> 00:21:44,778
(DinDin fell for it.)

629
00:21:45,448 --> 00:21:46,747
(DinDin loses by playing rock.)

630
00:21:46,748 --> 00:21:47,918
- See? Joon. Hey.
- See?

631
00:21:48,348 --> 00:21:52,558
(The round ends with a shocking result.)

632
00:21:55,558 --> 00:21:57,528
My gosh. See?

633
00:21:57,598 --> 00:21:59,167
- See?
- Joon. Hey.

634
00:21:59,168 --> 00:22:00,497
- Let's go big.
- Yes. Let's go big.

635
00:22:00,498 --> 00:22:01,897
- That's what I thought.
- He said we had no guts.

636
00:22:01,898 --> 00:22:03,138
- Earlier, Joon...
- We did it.

637
00:22:03,668 --> 00:22:06,007
(A huge shock)

638
00:22:06,008 --> 00:22:08,068
- Mouse Hunters won...
- That was good.

639
00:22:08,238 --> 00:22:10,078
- their second point.
- Audacity.

640
00:22:10,178 --> 00:22:11,737
- It was audacity.
- That was amazing.

641
00:22:11,738 --> 00:22:13,018
- We've got this.
- Let's do it.

642
00:22:13,308 --> 00:22:15,108
- This is insane.
- Didn't we win?

643
00:22:15,808 --> 00:22:17,317
- Didn't we win?
- It's over.

644
00:22:17,318 --> 00:22:18,677
- What? We won.
- In the end,

645
00:22:18,678 --> 00:22:20,117
Mouse Hunters have two papers left.

646
00:22:20,118 --> 00:22:21,118
- We won.
- What?

647
00:22:21,119 --> 00:22:22,817
- With 1 rock and 3 papers, - We won.

648
00:22:22,818 --> 00:22:23,887
DinDin...

649
00:22:23,888 --> 00:22:24,888
(Even if the game continues, DinDin would lose.)

650
00:22:24,889 --> 00:22:26,288
- He's defeated.
- We won.

651
00:22:28,988 --> 00:22:30,798
- Didn't we win?
- We won on our own.

652
00:22:30,998 --> 00:22:34,227
The remaining cards... The current score is 2 to 1.

653
00:22:34,228 --> 00:22:36,938
Even if they win with paper against rock,

654
00:22:37,138 --> 00:22:40,038
DinDin has only 1 rock and 3 papers.

655
00:22:40,238 --> 00:22:41,408
In this game...

656
00:22:41,438 --> 00:22:42,977
(Dopamine overload)

657
00:22:42,978 --> 00:22:44,837
Mouse Hunters take the victory.

658
00:22:44,838 --> 00:22:46,477
(Mouse Hunters are the final winner.)

659
00:22:46,478 --> 00:22:49,148
Catch the mouse, catch the mouse, Din Din Din

660
00:22:50,078 --> 00:22:52,317
(After the four of them spent the whole day chasing the mouse...)

661
00:22:52,318 --> 00:22:54,147
Mouse Hunters win.

662
00:22:54,148 --> 00:22:55,187
(They finally catch the mouse.)

663
00:22:55,188 --> 00:22:56,188
That was great.

664
00:22:56,818 --> 00:22:58,087
(Everyone celebrates the successful capture of the mouse.)

665
00:22:58,088 --> 00:22:59,488
That was an amazing victory.

666
00:22:59,728 --> 00:23:01,788
Let's hear from him. Please sit down.

667
00:23:02,428 --> 00:23:04,127
You played rock.

668
00:23:04,128 --> 00:23:05,897
Actually, we expected you to play...

669
00:23:05,898 --> 00:23:08,027
- paper.
- Exactly. Why did you do that?

670
00:23:08,028 --> 00:23:09,867
He probably thought that we'd play safe.

671
00:23:09,868 --> 00:23:11,797
Let's hear the loser's side...

672
00:23:11,798 --> 00:23:13,508
and what led to his decision.

673
00:23:16,108 --> 00:23:17,178
I feel devastated.

674
00:23:17,838 --> 00:23:18,838
I feel devastated.

675
00:23:18,839 --> 00:23:20,807
Come on. You only lost once.

676
00:23:20,808 --> 00:23:22,147
(DinDin got completely outsmarted, and he has no excuse.)

677
00:23:22,148 --> 00:23:23,247
Smile.

678
00:23:23,248 --> 00:23:24,547
Some of us lose nonstop.

679
00:23:24,548 --> 00:23:26,987
You only lost once. Lighten up.

680
00:23:26,988 --> 00:23:28,747
- Talk to us.
- DinDin is close to crying.

681
00:23:28,748 --> 00:23:30,687
Do you need a minute to talk?

682
00:23:30,688 --> 00:23:31,757
What do you think?

683
00:23:31,758 --> 00:23:33,958
- Personally...
- Yes?

684
00:23:35,588 --> 00:23:37,197
You must've learned something.

685
00:23:37,198 --> 00:23:39,097
It was fun.

686
00:23:39,098 --> 00:23:42,567
To be honest, doing the missions alone felt really lonely.

687
00:23:42,568 --> 00:23:44,338
- I see.
- I can understand.

688
00:23:48,108 --> 00:23:49,537
I wonder what they're doing.

689
00:23:49,538 --> 00:23:51,638
Being alone does feel lonely.

690
00:23:52,848 --> 00:23:53,878
Go.

691
00:23:54,008 --> 00:23:56,677
(DinDin tried not to show it, but he secretly wanted to be with them.)

692
00:23:56,678 --> 00:23:58,017
It was very lonely.

693
00:23:58,018 --> 00:24:03,088
I didn't want to appear like the dominant force.

694
00:24:03,418 --> 00:24:05,957
- We didn't want that either.
- We're family.

695
00:24:05,958 --> 00:24:08,528
When I lost this game,

696
00:24:09,828 --> 00:24:11,198
I felt disappointed...

697
00:24:11,798 --> 00:24:14,267
and relieved at the same time.

698
00:24:14,268 --> 00:24:15,667
- We're one team.
- I could see that.

699
00:24:15,668 --> 00:24:16,968
That's what I thought.

700
00:24:17,198 --> 00:24:18,768
DinDin, you just got emotional.

701
00:24:19,538 --> 00:24:21,737
Yes, he's tearing up.

702
00:24:21,738 --> 00:24:22,937
(He must've missed the members a lot.)

703
00:24:22,938 --> 00:24:24,177
We're one team.

704
00:24:24,178 --> 00:24:26,098
We'll put our autographs and exchange the cards.

705
00:24:26,578 --> 00:24:28,248
As a souvenir, please sign it.

706
00:24:28,448 --> 00:24:30,948
Write down your thoughts for today and exchange them.

707
00:24:31,178 --> 00:24:34,788
This is a beautiful scene where we become one team again.

708
00:24:36,088 --> 00:24:38,317
I haven't sweated under an air conditioner in a long time.

709
00:24:38,318 --> 00:24:39,687
I must've been very nervous.

710
00:24:39,688 --> 00:24:40,827
My goodness.

711
00:24:40,828 --> 00:24:43,998
"Let's do another high-five with paper. DinDin."

712
00:24:44,528 --> 00:24:45,658
That's what he wrote.

713
00:24:45,858 --> 00:24:47,167
He's becoming more human now.

714
00:24:47,168 --> 00:24:48,804
(Let's do another high-five with paper. DinDin)

715
00:24:48,828 --> 00:24:50,197
Let me take a look.

716
00:24:50,198 --> 00:24:51,918
(Team Mouse Hunters also finishes writing.)

717
00:24:52,598 --> 00:24:53,958
They wrote, "We caught the mouse."

718
00:24:55,008 --> 00:24:57,378
(We caught the mouse.)

719
00:24:57,708 --> 00:24:59,647
- Give each other a high-five.
- High-five.

720
00:24:59,648 --> 00:25:01,948
(Giving each other a high-five for an amazing match)

721
00:25:02,108 --> 00:25:03,417
- The game ended beautifully.
- I had fun.

722
00:25:03,418 --> 00:25:04,947
It was both entertaining and moving.

723
00:25:04,948 --> 00:25:06,018
It was meaningful.

724
00:25:07,748 --> 00:25:09,518
All right, everyone.

725
00:25:10,418 --> 00:25:12,087
Mouse Hunters who won...

726
00:25:12,088 --> 00:25:14,827
will take a break until dinner.

727
00:25:14,828 --> 00:25:16,198
- What?
- And...

728
00:25:17,328 --> 00:25:18,658
- Team DinDin.
- What?

729
00:25:18,998 --> 00:25:20,167
I'm not a team.

730
00:25:20,168 --> 00:25:21,398
(Nervous)

731
00:25:22,068 --> 00:25:24,668
We already got food for the winning team, but...

732
00:25:25,238 --> 00:25:26,307
Oh, no.

733
00:25:26,308 --> 00:25:28,514
- He has to go and pick gomchwi.
- The losing team will...

734
00:25:28,538 --> 00:25:29,937
- But I...
- pick gomchwi...

735
00:25:29,938 --> 00:25:31,337
and eat it.

736
00:25:31,338 --> 00:25:33,907
I'm so emotionally scarred right now...

737
00:25:33,908 --> 00:25:35,577
that I prefer fasting.

738
00:25:35,578 --> 00:25:37,058
(Suddenly feeling the pain of defeat)

739
00:25:38,018 --> 00:25:39,517
- The impact must be strong.
- It must be.

740
00:25:39,518 --> 00:25:41,517
- Well done, everyone.
- Yes.

741
00:25:41,518 --> 00:25:42,587
Pick a lot of gomchwi...

742
00:25:42,588 --> 00:25:43,987
- so we can enjoy it fresh.
- Gomchwi is fresh.

743
00:25:43,988 --> 00:25:45,117
- The valuable...
- This is no joke.

744
00:25:45,118 --> 00:25:46,858
We wrote down all the probabilities.

745
00:25:46,958 --> 00:25:48,728
We should get a good insert shot of that.

746
00:25:48,858 --> 00:25:50,338
All the probabilities could be wrong.

747
00:25:50,598 --> 00:25:52,718
- You're probably right.
- You calculated them wrong.

748
00:25:53,328 --> 00:25:54,598
That would be funny.

749
00:25:56,568 --> 00:25:58,498
- Please put on your gear first.
- What?

750
00:26:01,208 --> 00:26:02,208
Goodness.

751
00:26:03,108 --> 00:26:05,538
I lost on purpose to be with them.

752
00:26:07,748 --> 00:26:09,207
Keeping a social life is hard.

753
00:26:09,208 --> 00:26:10,888
(Grumbling while getting dressed for work)

754
00:26:12,518 --> 00:26:15,288
(Wobbling)

755
00:26:16,818 --> 00:26:18,558
Have you eaten gomchwi properly before?

756
00:26:19,158 --> 00:26:21,928
I don't remember eating gomchwi.

757
00:26:22,388 --> 00:26:25,058
What is gomchwi, anyway? I don't know what it is.

758
00:26:26,868 --> 00:26:30,067
(Soon, he arrives at a gomchwi farm.)

759
00:26:30,068 --> 00:26:31,568
How do I pick it?

760
00:26:31,798 --> 00:26:34,108
Avoid the young leaves.

761
00:26:34,568 --> 00:26:36,177
