00:34:44,758 --> 00:34:46,297
I served in the military in Cheorwon.

1017
00:34:46,298 --> 00:34:48,197
It's very close to Yanggu.

1018
00:34:48,198 --> 00:34:49,967
The winter is extremely harsh,

1019
00:34:49,968 --> 00:34:51,497
- This endured it.
- and it endured that.

1020
00:34:51,498 --> 00:34:53,667
It also had to survive the summer season.

1021
00:34:53,668 --> 00:34:55,267
The summer is also extremely hot.

1022
00:34:55,268 --> 00:34:58,337
It's impossible to find anything that grows stronger than this.

1023
00:34:58,338 --> 00:34:59,407
- Right.
- It's extremely resistant.

1024
00:34:59,408 --> 00:35:01,247
It's like you growing up in Canada.

1025
00:35:01,248 --> 00:35:03,418
- It's DinDin in the plant world.
- Yes.

1026
00:35:03,718 --> 00:35:05,148
May I have some fresh gomchwi?

1027
00:35:05,518 --> 00:35:06,888
Fresh gomchwi is really delicious.

1028
00:35:07,118 --> 00:35:08,187
One leaf isn't affectionate.

1029
00:35:08,188 --> 00:35:09,447
- I'll give you two.
- Of course.

1030
00:35:09,448 --> 00:35:10,888
Thank you. You're very affectionate.

1031
00:35:11,518 --> 00:35:13,217
Usually, affection goes both ways.

1032
00:35:13,218 --> 00:35:14,287
That's right.

1033
00:35:14,288 --> 00:35:15,728
The deep-fried gomchwi is very good.

1034
00:35:15,828 --> 00:35:17,227
Give him some deep-fried gomchwi since he gave me two.

1035
00:35:17,228 --> 00:35:18,228
(He finally tries the doenjang paste with fresh gomchwi.)

1036
00:35:18,229 --> 00:35:19,997
This beef doenjang paste...

1037
00:35:19,998 --> 00:35:21,927
It's very fresh, and the flavor is incomparable.

1038
00:35:21,928 --> 00:35:23,797
- When cooked, the flavor goes away.
- Right.

1039
00:35:23,798 --> 00:35:25,597
If I had to pick, I'd choose this and doenjang paste.

1040
00:35:25,598 --> 00:35:26,598
- Really?
- Yes.

1041
00:35:26,599 --> 00:35:27,968
All I need is this with kimchi.

1042
00:35:28,538 --> 00:35:31,538
Its flavor seems as strong as sesame leaves.

1043
00:35:31,908 --> 00:35:32,977
(Bear Se Yoon gets some gomchwi.)

1044
00:35:32,978 --> 00:35:34,077
The scent is strong.

1045
00:35:34,078 --> 00:35:35,208
What is he doing?

1046
00:35:35,348 --> 00:35:36,448
It's a thief.

1047
00:35:36,548 --> 00:35:38,877
These are mine. Give me 2 or 3 leaves.

1048
00:35:38,878 --> 00:35:41,088
- I'm sorry.
- They have a similar taste.

1049
00:35:41,288 --> 00:35:42,347
Right.

1050
00:35:42,348 --> 00:35:43,657
He knows how to enjoy it.

1051
00:35:43,658 --> 00:35:45,818
(It tastes good enough for a bear to get intoxicated.)

1052
00:35:46,358 --> 00:35:48,158
I bet it tastes very clean.

1053
00:35:48,588 --> 00:35:49,588
(Impressed)

1054
00:35:49,589 --> 00:35:50,828
Isn't it nice and clean?

1055
00:35:50,958 --> 00:35:53,228
It tastes better than meat. I mean it.

1056
00:35:54,198 --> 00:35:56,168
It might be hard to believe, but I'm serious.

1057
00:35:56,598 --> 00:35:58,337
- But I'd eat too much rice.
- It's clean.

1058
00:35:58,338 --> 00:35:59,467
Yes.

1059
00:35:59,468 --> 00:36:01,407
- In the mountain...
- The pieces of beef are big.

1060
00:36:01,408 --> 00:36:03,267
It feels like burying my face in the mountain in Yanggu.

1061
00:36:03,268 --> 00:36:04,478
Try the dumplings.

1062
00:36:04,778 --> 00:36:05,778
- Why?
- Are they good?

1063
00:36:05,778 --> 00:36:06,778
- They're so good.
- Dumplings.

1064
00:36:06,779 --> 00:36:09,277
- Give me some.
- They taste better than I thought.

1065
00:36:09,278 --> 00:36:10,347
- Really?
- Yes.

1066
00:36:10,348 --> 00:36:12,017
- The dumpling is well cooked.
- Dumplings.

1067
00:36:12,018 --> 00:36:13,317
There are dried radish greens inside.

1068
00:36:13,318 --> 00:36:15,547
(Dried radish green dumplings with a crispy seared bottom)

1069
00:36:15,548 --> 00:36:16,908
- It's really good.
- What's this?

1070
00:36:17,058 --> 00:36:18,758
It's so good that it's making me cry.

1071
00:36:19,188 --> 00:36:21,758
(Eating)

1072
00:36:22,188 --> 00:36:23,327
(It's needless to say.)

1073
00:36:23,328 --> 00:36:24,597
Its flavor is amazing.

1074
00:36:24,598 --> 00:36:26,627
- These are amazing. Inside...
- This is it.

1075
00:36:26,628 --> 00:36:28,098
The dumpling is so fragrant.

1076
00:36:28,428 --> 00:36:31,737
The natural aroma of dried radish greens spreads.

1077
00:36:31,738 --> 00:36:33,708
It clears the nose and the respiratory system.

1078
00:36:34,408 --> 00:36:36,937
This is gopchang hot pot with dried radish greens.

1079
00:36:36,938 --> 00:36:39,038
What should I start with? Everything is so good.

1080
00:36:39,208 --> 00:36:40,208
(Impressed)

1081
00:36:40,209 --> 00:36:41,608
- Is it rich?
- Jong Min.

1082
00:36:41,808 --> 00:36:44,418
Usually, there are dried radish greens in gamjatang.

1083
00:36:45,118 --> 00:36:46,817
We always get an extra order.

1084
00:36:46,818 --> 00:36:49,387
This is the upgraded,

1085
00:36:49,388 --> 00:36:50,518
high-end version.

1086
00:36:51,258 --> 00:36:52,688
This is rare.

1087
00:36:52,818 --> 00:36:54,258
- Jong Min.
- Yes?

1088
00:36:54,458 --> 00:36:56,157
How is the gopchang hot pot with dried radish greens?

1089
00:36:56,158 --> 00:36:57,298
Gosh.

1090
00:36:57,428 --> 00:36:59,527
The dried radish greens soaked up all the broth.

1091
00:36:59,528 --> 00:37:01,928
In one bite, I get both the greens and the broth.

1092
00:37:02,528 --> 00:37:03,767
You're right.

1093
00:37:03,768 --> 00:37:05,398
- Right?
- Can they be separated?

1094
00:37:07,508 --> 00:37:08,508
- Is it possible?
- No.

1095
00:37:08,509 --> 00:37:10,749
- It requires skill.
- It's impossible to separate them.

1096
00:37:11,078 --> 00:37:12,877
The flavor is...

1097
00:37:12,878 --> 00:37:14,154
(He ends up bursting out laughing.)

1098
00:37:14,178 --> 00:37:15,907
Just the dried radish greens alone...

1099
00:37:15,908 --> 00:37:17,577
taste like a braised dish.

1100
00:37:17,578 --> 00:37:19,247
As they're soaked with broth,

1101
00:37:19,248 --> 00:37:21,587
- Totally.
- they're perfect with rice.

1102
00:37:21,588 --> 00:37:22,617
- I agree.
- It's very delicious.

1103
00:37:22,618 --> 00:37:23,887
Tonight's food is seriously good.

1104
00:37:23,888 --> 00:37:25,017
Deep-fried gomchwi is excellent.

1105
00:37:25,018 --> 00:37:27,127
This is the best food I ever had.

1106
00:37:27,128 --> 00:37:28,357
It's the best.

1107
00:37:28,358 --> 00:37:30,528
- We ate everything.
- We cleaned the plates.

1108
00:37:31,028 --> 00:37:32,028
I'm glad to hear that.

1109
00:37:32,029 --> 00:37:33,397
- We cleared most of the plates.
- Yes.

1110
00:37:33,398 --> 00:37:34,398
(They finished everything before realizing it.)

1111
00:37:34,399 --> 00:37:36,937
All you need is gomchwi with doenjang paste.

1112
00:37:36,938 --> 00:37:39,168
- Seriously.
- He's just like a bear.

1113
00:37:39,638 --> 00:37:41,208
He's a bear eating gomchwi.

1114
00:37:41,238 --> 00:37:42,608
The bear is eating gomchwi.

1115
00:37:43,268 --> 00:37:45,877
Sleeping Indoors or Outdoors is next.

1116
00:37:45,878 --> 00:37:47,578
- Okay.
- We'll see you when it's ready.

1117
00:37:47,678 --> 00:37:50,618
We savored the taste of spring to the last bite...

1118
00:37:50,778 --> 00:37:52,047
since we had gomchwi.

1119
00:37:52,048 --> 00:37:53,894
(On to the next schedule after recharging with spring flavors)

1120
00:37:53,918 --> 00:37:54,988
What's this?

1121
00:37:55,648 --> 00:37:56,688
What is it?

1122
00:37:56,858 --> 00:37:59,188
Is this where we're sleeping?

1123
00:37:59,488 --> 00:38:01,457
This must be where we sleep indoors.

1124
00:38:01,458 --> 00:38:02,458
- Right?
- Yes.

1125
00:38:02,459 --> 00:38:03,697
- It's here.
- This is nice.

1126
00:38:03,698 --> 00:38:06,027
All five of us can definitely sleep here.

1127
00:38:06,028 --> 00:38:07,097
That's true.

1128
00:38:07,098 --> 00:38:10,338
This is where you'll be sleeping tonight.

1129
00:38:10,868 --> 00:38:14,067
The charming bunk beds here caught our attention.

1130
00:38:14,068 --> 00:38:16,167
So tonight,

1131
00:38:16,168 --> 00:38:18,708
to bring back the memories of a school retreat,

1132
00:38:19,208 --> 00:38:21,707
all of you will be sleeping in bunk beds.

1133
00:38:21,708 --> 00:38:22,877
- Really?
- What?

1134
00:38:22,878 --> 00:38:23,978
Are you serious?

1135
00:38:24,518 --> 00:38:25,647
He's lying.

1136
00:38:25,648 --> 00:38:28,788
Your bunk beds are located in this room and...

1137
00:38:29,518 --> 00:38:31,058
(And?)

1138
00:38:31,218 --> 00:38:34,487
They're also outside where it's cool.

1139
00:38:34,488 --> 00:38:35,727
The bunk beds?

1140
00:38:35,728 --> 00:38:37,304
That's sleeping outdoors without a tent.

1141
00:38:37,328 --> 00:38:39,234
- Without a tent?
- It's sleeping without a tent.

1142
00:38:39,258 --> 00:38:40,468
Sleeping without a tent?

1143
00:38:41,328 --> 00:38:42,368
Yes.

1144
00:38:42,668 --> 00:38:44,637
- Hey, we're in Gangwon Province.
- Mister.

1145
00:38:44,638 --> 00:38:46,768
- I've never done it before.
- We're in Yanggu.

1146
00:38:47,438 --> 00:38:49,368
The director is wearing a long, padded jacket.

1147
00:38:49,668 --> 00:38:51,877
(The current temperature is 5°C, it's clearly cold.)

1148
00:38:51,878 --> 00:38:52,937
- I mean...
- Mister.

1149
00:38:52,938 --> 00:38:54,848
The bunk beds are right here.

1150
00:38:55,408 --> 00:38:56,678
They're right in the front.

1151
00:38:56,878 --> 00:38:58,678
- What?
- This is the worst.

1152
00:39:03,218 --> 00:39:05,387
- One person on top and the bottom?
- We will be...

1153
00:39:05,388 --> 00:39:06,457
- exposed to the cold air.
- Seriously?

1154
00:39:06,458 --> 00:39:07,957
- Are you telling us to sleep there?
- We're very exposed.

1155
00:39:07,958 --> 00:39:09,587
- That will be extremely cold.
- That's crazy.

1156
00:39:09,588 --> 00:39:10,927
- Where are they?
- This is terrible.

1157
00:39:10,928 --> 00:39:12,527
- This is crazy.
- Where are they?

1158
00:39:12,528 --> 00:39:14,428
- Out in the open...
- Where are they?

1159
00:39:14,698 --> 00:39:16,727
(Only DinDin can't see the bunk beds.)

1160
00:39:16,728 --> 00:39:17,837
Where are they?

1161
00:39:17,838 --> 00:39:19,867
(I want to see them too.)

1162
00:39:19,868 --> 00:39:21,107
There they are.

1163
00:39:21,108 --> 00:39:22,207
(I want to see the bunk beds.)

1164
00:39:22,208 --> 00:39:25,277
(It's quite hard for him to look outside the window.)

1165
00:39:25,278 --> 00:39:27,007
(Din Mario also witnesses the bunk beds.)

1166
00:39:27,008 --> 00:39:29,577
You'll play Sleeping Indoors or Outdoors...

1167
00:39:29,578 --> 00:39:32,217
to determine the location of your bed.

1168
00:39:32,218 --> 00:39:33,617
Sleeping outdoors without a tent?

1169
00:39:33,618 --> 00:39:35,388
Tonight's Sleeping Indoors or Outdoors is...

1170
00:39:35,518 --> 00:39:38,198
a classic game on 2 Days 1 Night that we haven't played in a while.

1171
00:39:38,558 --> 00:39:40,388
It's Zombie Game.

1172
00:39:40,828 --> 00:39:42,328
Zombie Game?

1173
00:39:42,888 --> 00:39:44,027
We can't get bitten.

1174
00:39:44,028 --> 00:39:45,358
I'm bad at that.

1175
00:39:45,658 --> 00:39:47,597
- It's scary with my eyes covered.
- It's scary.

1176
00:39:47,598 --> 00:39:49,228
Joon, they won't be covered completely.

1177
00:39:49,528 --> 00:39:51,798
Each of you will take turns.

1178
00:39:52,468 --> 00:39:55,267
The four of you will become zombies.

1179
00:39:55,268 --> 00:39:57,637
With your eyes covered, you'll catch the remaining one.

1180
00:39:57,638 --> 00:40:00,007
- Four of us will be zombies?
- They catch one person.

1181
00:40:00,008 --> 00:40:01,008
Right.

1182
00:40:01,009 --> 00:40:02,408
Two members who get bitten...

1183
00:40:02,708 --> 00:40:05,077
by the zombies and shout the earliest.

1184
00:40:05,078 --> 00:40:06,377
(2 members who get caught by the zombies the earliest)

1185
00:40:06,378 --> 00:40:08,617
You will sleep on the bunk beds outdoors.

1186
00:40:08,618 --> 00:40:10,858
- You'll measure the time?
- That's correct.

1187
00:40:11,058 --> 00:40:12,958
- Gosh, this is...
- How long will you survive?

1188
00:40:13,688 --> 00:40:17,227
However, the one who avoids the zombies must wear...

1189
00:40:17,228 --> 00:40:18,427
slippers with bells.

1190
00:40:18,428 --> 00:40:19,428
(A weakness for the human)

1191
00:40:19,429 --> 00:40:21,328
Shall we start biting each other?

1192
00:40:21,868 --> 00:40:23,397
- Do I wear them from the start?
- Yes.

1193
00:40:23,398 --> 00:40:24,537
- From the start?
- Yes.

1194
00:40:24,538 --> 00:40:26,398
(Player 1, Moon Se Yoon)

1195
00:40:26,568 --> 00:40:28,237
Here's one way to catch him fast.

1196
00:40:28,238 --> 00:40:29,307
We should...

1197
00:40:29,308 --> 00:40:30,577
We should hold each other's hand.

1198
00:40:30,578 --> 00:40:32,677
We must go in while spreading out.

1199
00:40:32,678 --> 00:40:33,877
Let's say that we're inside.

1200
00:40:33,878 --> 00:40:35,377
Spread out. Are you spread out?

1201
00:40:35,378 --> 00:40:37,247
- Keep going like this.
- Swing your legs too.

1202
00:40:37,248 --> 00:40:38,477
- Swing them.
- Swing them.

1203
00:40:38,478 --> 00:40:39,577
- Just the legs.
- Right.

1204
00:40:39,578 --> 00:40:41,347
- So that he can't escape.
- Keep going while moving the legs.

1205
00:40:41,348 --> 00:40:42,717
After that,

1206
00:40:42,718 --> 00:40:44,957
- we'll hear the bell sound.
- Right.

1207
00:40:44,958 --> 00:40:47,157
- Shouldn't we separate ways then?
- Okay.

1208
00:40:47,158 --> 00:40:49,187
Once you catch him, call everyone before biting him.

1209
00:40:49,188 --> 00:40:50,757
- "I caught him."
- It's possible for Se Yoon...

1210
00:40:50,758 --> 00:40:52,757
- to use his strength to break away.
- After letting everyone know...

1211
00:40:52,758 --> 00:40:54,127
- Once someone catches him, - We'll go in that direction.

1212
00:40:54,128 --> 00:40:55,927
Shout out loud. Then we'll come to you.

1213
00:40:55,928 --> 00:40:57,038
Okay.

1214
00:40:57,938 --> 00:40:59,138
Here's what I'll do.

1215
00:40:59,598 --> 00:41:00,938
After staying still,

1216
00:41:01,408 --> 00:41:03,908
if I manage to avoid twice, I won't place last.

1217
00:41:04,878 --> 00:41:05,978
I've got this.

1218
00:41:06,478 --> 00:41:08,507
You blocked everywhere so that I can't sit.

1219
00:41:08,508 --> 00:41:10,789
- Will it be hard to sleep outside?
- It'll be very hard.

1220
00:41:10,848 --> 00:41:11,917
Let's stay focused.

1221
00:41:11,918 --> 00:41:13,348
- Okay.
- Once you hear the sound,

1222
00:41:13,378 --> 00:41:14,517
follow it.

1223
00:41:14,518 --> 00:41:16,387
We'll get started. Get ready.

1224
00:41:16,388 --> 00:41:17,708
(For how long will Se Yoon last?)

1225
00:41:18,758 --> 00:41:20,887
- Let's go.
- Be careful.

1226
00:41:20,888 --> 00:41:22,058
There are beds in the front.

1227
00:41:22,228 --> 00:41:23,587
Be careful. There are beds in the front.

1228
00:41:23,588 --> 00:41:24,957
- Spread out.
- Spread out.

1229
00:41:24,958 --> 00:41:26,427
- Jong Min, are you inside?
- Yes.

1230
00:41:26,428 --> 00:41:27,597
Are you inside?

1231
00:41:27,598 --> 00:41:29,027
- Are we good?
- He's on the left.

1232
00:41:29,028 --> 00:41:31,968
(The group of zombies approaches Se Yoon.)

1233
00:41:32,368 --> 00:41:33,707
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

1234
00:41:33,708 --> 00:41:35,708
(Nervous)

1235
00:41:35,838 --> 00:41:38,119
You don't hear anything, right? He must be near this bed.

1236
00:41:39,178 --> 00:41:40,208
Go forward.

1237
00:41:40,548 --> 00:41:41,808
Go all the way in.

1238
00:41:42,178 --> 00:41:44,918
(Se Yoon is staying still while holding his breath.)

1239
00:41:45,448 --> 00:41:47,917
(Moving away from the beds and trying to surround the target)

1240
00:41:47,918 --> 00:41:49,147
- I'm scared.
- Move forward.

1241
00:41:49,148 --> 00:41:51,588
(DinDin is getting closer to Se Yoon.)

1242
00:41:51,958 --> 00:41:53,827
Go back.

1243
00:41:53,828 --> 00:41:55,787
(Gosh, go away!)

1244
00:41:55,788 --> 00:41:57,327
- Go forward.
- I haven't moved yet.

1245
00:41:57,328 --> 00:41:58,527
- He's here.
- I haven't moved yet.

1246
00:41:58,528 --> 00:42:00,367
(DinDin's hand touches his belly.)

1247
00:42:00,368 --> 00:42:01,667
He's here. I caught him.

1248
00:42:01,668 --> 00:42:03,068
Catch him.

1249
00:42:03,098 --> 00:42:04,597
- Catch him.
- I caught him.

1250
00:42:04,598 --> 00:42:05,598
Oh, gosh. It's dangerous.

1251
00:42:05,598 --> 00:42:06,598
I might get hurt.

1252
00:42:06,599 --> 00:42:08,344
(Did he catch him, or is he being dragged around?)

1253
00:42:08,368 --> 00:42:10,167
(Will Se Yoon fight off the zombies with sheer strength?)

1254
00:42:10,168 --> 00:42:11,277
Hey, we might get hurt at this rate.

1255
00:42:11,278 --> 00:42:12,278
(They're fighting him head-on.)

1256
00:42:12,278 --> 00:42:13,278
Hey, we might get hurt at this rate.

1257
00:42:13,279 --> 00:42:14,307
(Pushing them away with his belly)

1258
00:42:14,308 --> 00:42:15,748
(Pinching)

1259
00:42:16,778 --> 00:42:18,978
(The moment they pinch him, a sorrowful cry resonates.)

1260
00:42:19,678 --> 00:42:22,718
(Moon Se Yoon got caught.)

1261
00:42:23,788 --> 00:42:25,257
(Worn out)

1262
00:42:25,258 --> 00:42:26,488
It ended so quickly.

1263
00:42:26,718 --> 00:42:27,728
What's my record?

1264
00:42:28,028 --> 00:42:29,827
- All right.
- I think it's about 13 seconds.

1265
00:42:29,828 --> 00:42:30,828
(What could be Se Yoon's record?)

1266
00:42:30,829 --> 00:42:32,257
- Will you announce it later?
- Shall I?

1267
00:42:32,258 --> 00:42:33,967
- What do you say?
- Announce it later.

1268
00:42:33,968 --> 00:42:35,027
This is like...

1269
00:42:35,028 --> 00:42:36,297
This is like a 100m race.

1270
00:42:36,298 --> 00:42:38,338
- It's a matter of split seconds.
- That's right.

1271
00:42:38,668 --> 00:42:41,038
We need to hold out for just a second longer.

1272
00:42:41,368 --> 00:42:42,937
- Come on out.
- Okay.

1273
00:42:42,938 --> 00:42:44,337
- Let's talk outside.
- Okay.

1274
00:42:44,338 --> 00:42:45,438
Let's talk outside.

1275
00:42:46,438 --> 00:42:47,778
Should I try this?

1276
00:42:48,548 --> 00:42:51,048
(He walks in a crouching position to avoid making noises.)

1277
00:42:51,448 --> 00:42:53,047
(Will he be able to evade the zombies without making noises?)

1278
00:42:53,048 --> 00:42:54,987
- Will I get caught?
- You can just dodge them at once.

1279
00:42:54,988 --> 00:42:57,457
When we go into the room,

1280
00:42:57,458 --> 00:42:59,617
he can hide in the corner where the beds are,

1281
00:42:59,618 --> 00:43:00,787
in the corner where I was standing earlier,

1282
00:43:00,788 --> 00:43:03,188
or beside the fridge. There are only those three spots.

1283
00:43:06,758 --> 00:43:09,497
(Just as he expected, Seon Ho stands beside the fridge.)

1284
00:43:09,498 --> 00:43:11,938
I'll go and check clear to the corner along the beds.

1285
00:43:12,368 --> 00:43:13,837
One of the two of you should check around the fridge.

1286
00:43:13,838 --> 00:43:15,207
- Then Se Yoon...
- There's only the center spot left.

1287
00:43:15,208 --> 00:43:16,584
Then we don't have to line up while holding hands.

1288
00:43:16,608 --> 00:43:18,078
Right. We don't have to do that.

1289
00:43:18,908 --> 00:43:20,447
- Okay.
- Se Yoon, go first.

1290
00:43:20,448 --> 00:43:22,054
- Se Yoon will lead the way.
- I'll lead the way.

1291
00:43:22,078 --> 00:43:23,147
All right. Here we go.

1292
00:43:23,148 --> 00:43:24,547
(How long will Seon Ho be able to hold out?)

1293
00:43:24,548 --> 00:43:26,748
- Ready.
- Should I check near the fridge?

1294
00:43:27,388 --> 00:43:28,588
Should I check there?

1295
00:43:28,948 --> 00:43:29,948
Be careful.

1296
00:43:29,949 --> 00:43:30,957
(Round 2 starts.)

1297
00:43:30,958 --> 00:43:32,018
Should I check there?

1298
00:43:32,088 --> 00:43:33,987
(Zombie Se Yoon runs into the room as they planned.)

1299
00:43:33,988 --> 00:43:35,427
- Will you check the spot?
- Yes, I will.

1300
00:43:35,428 --> 00:43:36,428
Be careful.

1301
00:43:36,429 --> 00:43:38,927
(Seon Ho is not in Se Yoon's line of sight.)

1302
00:43:38,928 --> 00:43:40,967
Catch him. Get him.

1303
00:43:40,968 --> 00:43:42,204
(The other members quickly start hunting as well.)

1304
00:43:42,228 --> 00:43:43,567
- This is it.
- Catch him.

1305
00:43:43,568 --> 00:43:44,568
(DinDin runs toward the fridge right away.)

1306
00:43:44,569 --> 00:43:45,698
- This is it.
- Catch him.

1307
00:43:46,468 --> 00:43:47,838
- Who is this?
- It's me.

1308
00:43:48,568 --> 00:43:49,568
Is he not there?

1309
00:43:51,738 --> 00:43:54,048
(Seon Ho isn't at any of the three spots they expected!)

1310
00:43:54,808 --> 00:43:57,008
(As Seon Ho is not where they expected him to be...)

1311
00:43:57,518 --> 00:44:00,548
- Oh, he's here.
- No, it's me.

1312
00:44:01,518 --> 00:44:03,448
(They start acting weird.)

1313
00:44:03,888 --> 00:44:04,957
(Shouting for no reason)

1314
00:44:04,958 --> 00:44:06,078
Why can't I hear him moving?

1315
00:44:06,718 --> 00:44:09,327
(However...)

1316
00:44:09,328 --> 00:44:11,698
(Seon Ho is nowhere to be seen in the room.)

1317
00:44:12,158 --> 00:44:14,600
(Where on earth is Seon Ho?)

1318
00:44:14,703 --> 00:44:15,405
- Why can't I hear him moving?
- Did you check the beds?

1319
00:44:15,703 --> 00:44:16,703
Yes, he's not here.

1320
00:44:17,109 --> 00:44:21,518
(He thoroughly searches the bed.)

1321
00:44:21,519 --> 00:44:23,065
- Why can't I hear him moving?
- Did you check the beds?

1322
00:44:23,089 --> 00:44:24,349
He's not here.

1323
00:44:25,619 --> 00:44:28,419
(Seon Ho is hiding under the bed!)

1324
00:44:28,959 --> 00:44:31,188
(Se Yoon came so close to him.)

1325
00:44:31,189 --> 00:44:32,358
He's not here.

1326
00:44:32,359 --> 00:44:33,728
(Se Yoon's foot doesn't reach him, missing by a whisker.)

1327
00:44:33,729 --> 00:44:34,899
Wait. On the right side.

1328
00:44:35,699 --> 00:44:36,699
This way.

1329
00:44:36,700 --> 00:44:37,729
(He survived!)

1330
00:44:37,899 --> 00:44:39,238
This way.

1331
00:44:39,239 --> 00:44:40,438
(And...)

1332
00:44:40,439 --> 00:44:42,168
(The zombies keep acting weird.)

1333
00:44:42,169 --> 00:44:43,169
Who is this?

1334
00:44:43,709 --> 00:44:45,408
("Where are you, Seon Ho?" He sticks his tongue out.)

1335
00:44:45,409 --> 00:44:47,739
Gosh, I can't... Oh, boy. It hurts so much.

1336
00:44:48,779 --> 00:44:49,779
- Who is this?
- It's me.

1337
00:44:49,849 --> 00:44:51,209
- Who is this?
- I said it was me.

1338
00:44:51,709 --> 00:44:52,818
Where did he go?

1339
00:44:52,819 --> 00:44:53,819
(They search the floor.)

1340
00:44:53,820 --> 00:44:54,978
It's me.

1341
00:44:54,979 --> 00:44:56,049
Where did he go?

1342
00:44:57,549 --> 00:44:58,719
Why can't I hear him moving?

1343
00:44:59,359 --> 00:45:01,565
- He must be muffling the bells.
- I think that's the case.

1344
00:45:01,589 --> 00:45:02,758
Guys, I can't hear the bells.

1345
00:45:02,759 --> 00:45:05,239
- Why can't I hear the bells?
- He must be muffling the bells.

1346
00:45:05,389 --> 00:45:06,599
I guess he'll sleep in here.

1347
00:45:07,029 --> 00:45:08,858
- Seon Ho, congratulations.
- No, guys.

1348
00:45:08,859 --> 00:45:10,499
You don't know yet.

1349
00:45:10,869 --> 00:45:12,068
- Hey.
- Wait. Who is this?

1350
00:45:12,069 --> 00:45:13,169
- It's me.
- Don't give up.

1351
00:45:13,539 --> 00:45:16,509
(Right then, DinDin creeps toward the bed.)

1352
00:45:16,909 --> 00:45:19,809
(Mouthing a scream)

1353
00:45:20,839 --> 00:45:22,548
(Finally, DinDin caught him.)

1354
00:45:22,549 --> 00:45:23,609
DinDin.

1355
00:45:24,679 --> 00:45:26,449
(Yoo Seon Ho got caught.)

1356
00:45:26,819 --> 00:45:28,919
(Seon Ho, where were you hiding?)

1357
00:45:29,149 --> 00:45:31,288
So, he was moving around right underneath us.

1358
00:45:31,289 --> 00:45:32,858
I didn't even move around.

1359
00:45:32,859 --> 00:45:33,859
I stayed still.

1360
00:45:33,860 --> 00:45:34,959
- Where?
- Here.

1361
00:45:35,059 --> 00:45:36,989
You guys didn't reach out far enough.

1362
00:45:37,629 --> 00:45:38,935
I was all the way back against the wall.

1363
00:45:38,959 --> 00:45:40,928
(You should've searched further back toward the wall.)

1364
00:45:40,929 --> 00:45:43,968
As a fatty, I could never have guessed his strategy.

1365
00:45:43,969 --> 00:45:45,298
It was a risky plan.

1366
00:45:45,299 --> 00:45:46,468
It would've been game over the second I got caught.

1367
00:45:46,469 --> 00:45:47,498
(Seon Ho's risky plan worked perfectly.)

1368
00:45:47,499 --> 00:45:48,599
This isn't easy.

1369
00:45:49,039 --> 00:45:50,469
Who else can fit under the bed?

1370
00:45:51,039 --> 00:45:52,879
- There's only one.
- DinDin.

1371
00:45:53,009 --> 00:45:54,708
This time, we'll check under the bed first.

1372
00:45:54,709 --> 00:45:56,878
- I'll search under the beds.
- I was going to hide under there.

1373
00:45:56,879 --> 00:45:58,048
(Seon Ho beat him to it.)

1374
00:45:58,049 --> 00:45:59,955
That went well. I'll probably be high up in the rankings.

1375
00:45:59,979 --> 00:46:01,079
You did a great job.

1376
00:46:01,449 --> 00:46:03,595
We just have to catch him quickly. I'll run this time.

1377
00:46:03,619 --> 00:46:04,649
- Hey.
- Let's go.

1378
00:46:04,949 --> 00:46:06,518
Where will you go first? Let us know where you'll go.

1379
00:46:06,519 --> 00:46:07,688
I'll search around the fridge.

1380
00:46:07,689 --> 00:46:09,088
- The fridge?
- That's not necessary.

1381
00:46:09,089 --> 00:46:11,558
- I'll search around all the beds.
- Okay. Check under the beds.

1382
00:46:11,559 --> 00:46:12,798
- You should come behind me.
- I'll check everywhere around them.

1383
00:46:12,799 --> 00:46:14,159
You come behind me.

1384
00:46:14,259 --> 00:46:15,828
- Where will you go?
- I'll go this way.

1385
00:46:15,829 --> 00:46:17,428
- I'll head toward the window first.
- The window?

1386
00:46:17,429 --> 00:46:18,798
You check around the fridge.

1387
00:46:18,799 --> 00:46:20,545
- And let's gather in the center.
- The fridge...

1388
00:46:20,569 --> 00:46:22,369
(At that time, Jong Min...)

1389
00:46:22,539 --> 00:46:24,539
(Thinking hard)

1390
00:46:26,539 --> 00:46:29,609
(He picks up a blanket.)

1391
00:46:30,509 --> 00:46:32,479
(Then he covers his foot with it?)

1392
00:46:33,249 --> 00:46:34,249
This is great.

1393
00:46:34,250 --> 00:46:35,479
Will this muffle the bells?

1394
00:46:35,779 --> 00:46:37,719
I can hear them, but they're not loud.

1395
00:46:39,559 --> 00:46:41,218
I'll show them what I've got.

1396
00:46:41,219 --> 00:46:43,135
(His strategy is to keep the bells from ringing.)

1397
00:46:43,159 --> 00:46:44,959
Oh, good. Nice.

1398
00:46:46,059 --> 00:46:48,599
(He takes slow, deliberate steps.)

1399
00:46:49,429 --> 00:46:52,899
(The bells are not ringing.)

1400
00:46:53,169 --> 00:46:56,809
(Eureka!)

1401
00:46:56,939 --> 00:47:03,179
(Jong Min, the master of stealth, walks around the room freely.)

1402
00:47:03,349 --> 00:47:04,608
(How long will he hold out with his bell-muffling strategy?)

1403
00:47:04,609 --> 00:47:06,349
All right. We'll begin!

1404
00:47:06,919 --> 00:47:08,118
Ready!

1405
00:47:08,119 --> 00:47:11,089
(How long will he hold out with his bell-muffling strategy?)

1406
00:47:11,589 --> 00:47:12,589
Let's be careful so that no one gets hurt.

1407
00:47:12,590 --> 00:47:14,288
Hold Se Yoon. You should hold him.

1408
00:47:14,289 --> 00:47:15,988
(Round 3 starts.)

1409
00:47:15,989 --> 00:47:16,989
- So that no one gets hurt.
- Hold Se Yoon.

1410
00:47:16,990 --> 00:47:18,889
(Jong Min throws pillows at them.)

1411
00:47:18,989 --> 00:47:21,059
(Go away!)

1412
00:47:21,299 --> 00:47:25,368
(The horde of zombies keeps moving while getting hit with pillows.)

1413
00:47:25,369 --> 00:47:26,369
Where is he?

1414
00:47:27,239 --> 00:47:28,868
He must be around here. He just hit me.

1415
00:47:28,869 --> 00:47:31,239
(They head to their assigned spots in an orderly fashion.)

1416
00:47:31,739 --> 00:47:35,679
(They start searching thoroughly.)

1417
00:47:36,079 --> 00:47:37,878
(Jong Min)

1418
00:47:37,879 --> 00:47:42,279
(Jong Min is surrounded by the zombies.)

1419
00:47:43,589 --> 00:47:44,888
(He navigates his way between the zombies.)

1420
00:47:44,889 --> 00:47:46,789
- He just hit me.
- Where is he?

1421
00:47:47,359 --> 00:47:52,558
(He carefully moves to prevent the bells from ringing.)

1422
00:47:52,559 --> 00:47:54,558
- Oh, wait.
- It's me.

1423
00:47:54,559 --> 00:47:55,969
He's not under the beds here.

1424
00:47:56,369 --> 00:47:57,498
- We're doomed.
- He's not under the beds.

1425
00:47:57,499 --> 00:47:59,098
- I found him.
- It's me.

1426
00:47:59,099 --> 00:48:00,099
(The zombies didn't notice Jong Min walking past them.)

1427
00:48:00,100 --> 00:48:04,409
(Relieved)

1428
00:48:04,909 --> 00:48:06,638
(Jong Min is hiding himself in the corner.)

1429
00:48:06,639 --> 00:48:08,508
- He's not under the beds.
- He's not here.

1430
00:48:08,509 --> 00:48:09,579
Where is he?

1431
00:48:10,149 --> 00:48:11,978
- He's hiding somewhere.
- I don't hear the bells.

1432
00:48:11,979 --> 00:48:13,018
He's not moving.

1433
00:48:13,019 --> 00:48:14,079
He's staying still.

1434
00:48:16,419 --> 00:48:19,459
(Zombie Se Yoon got so close to Jong Min!)

1435
00:48:19,689 --> 00:48:23,328
(There's nowhere to go to run from Se Yoon!)

1436
00:48:23,329 --> 00:48:24,329
He's staying still.

1437
00:48:24,330 --> 00:48:29,099
(Will he be caught just like this?)

1438
00:48:30,529 --> 00:48:32,168
Guys, I think he's around here.

1439
00:48:32,169 --> 00:48:33,339
- Where?
- I hear something.

1440
00:48:34,339 --> 00:48:37,409
(Should I go to the other side?)

1441
00:48:37,769 --> 00:48:41,709
(Jong Min survived.)

1442
00:48:42,009 --> 00:48:46,378
(Zombie Se Yoon goes away as DinDin shouts.)

1443
00:48:46,379 --> 00:48:47,418
(Jong Min)

1444
00:48:47,419 --> 00:48:50,419
(Jong Min barely survived thanks to DinDin's unexpected help.)

1445
00:48:50,489 --> 00:48:51,849
- Who is this?
- It's me.

1446
00:48:54,259 --> 00:48:55,888
- It's you, right?
- It's me. Who is this?

1447
00:48:55,889 --> 00:48:56,928
- Oh, what?
- It's me.

1448
00:48:56,929 --> 00:48:58,729
- Is it you?
- He's definitely under the bed.

1449
00:48:59,359 --> 00:49:01,119
I already checked. He wasn't under the beds.

1450
00:49:02,559 --> 00:49:03,768
He'll probably sleep indoors.

1451
00:49:03,769 --> 00:49:04,868
(Wiping the floor with his entire body)

1452
00:49:04,869 --> 00:49:06,349
- He's not here.
- What? Who is this?

1453
00:49:06,969 --> 00:49:08,298
He's not here. Is he not under the other bed?

1454
00:49:08,299 --> 00:49:10,868
(The four zombies are roaming around the same spots...)

1455
00:49:10,869 --> 00:49:13,438
(while Jong Min is right in front of them.)

1456
00:49:13,439 --> 00:49:15,315
- He's not under the beds.
- I don't hear the bells.

1457
00:49:15,339 --> 00:49:17,049
I checked under every bed. He's not there.

1458
00:49:17,179 --> 00:49:19,349
Wait. He's in the bottom bunk.

1459
00:49:19,519 --> 00:49:21,399
- In the bottom bunk... Who is this?
- It's me.

1460
00:49:21,579 --> 00:49:23,018
He keeps throwing things at me from the bottom bunk.

1461
00:49:23,019 --> 00:49:24,395
(When the zombies swarm around the corner...)

1462
00:49:24,419 --> 00:49:25,859
- Oh, wait.
- Hey, don't sleep here.

1463
00:49:26,159 --> 00:49:27,435
(Once again, he weaves his way through the zombies.)

1464
00:49:27,459 --> 00:49:28,858
- Up on the top bunk...
- Be quiet.

1465
00:49:28,859 --> 00:49:29,959
Okay. Let's quiet down.

1466
00:49:30,329 --> 00:49:34,258
(The zombies couldn't notice him even when he walked past them.)

1467
00:49:34,259 --> 00:49:36,428
- On the right side.
- He's on the left side.

1468
00:49:36,429 --> 00:49:37,468
(This is the true class of the 2 Days 1 Night veteran.)

1469
00:49:37,469 --> 00:49:38,499
Oh, he's here.

1470
00:49:38,729 --> 00:49:39,938
- Where are you going?
- It's me.

1471
00:49:39,939 --> 00:49:41,869
- Hey.
- Wait. I can hear the bells.

1472
00:49:41,939 --> 00:49:43,208
I bet he covered his feet with something.

1473
00:49:43,209 --> 00:49:44,308
(Attacking a zombie)

1474
00:49:44,309 --> 00:49:46,139
Someone just hit me on the forehead.

1475
00:49:46,779 --> 00:49:47,908
On the right side.

1476
00:49:47,909 --> 00:49:50,478
(Jong Min even sneaks up and gooses a zombie.)

1477
00:49:50,479 --> 00:49:53,748
(Jong Min's camera)

1478
00:49:53,749 --> 00:49:54,918
What happened? What's going on?

1479
00:49:54,919 --> 00:49:57,748
(The zombies are left helpless under his attack.)

1480
00:49:57,749 --> 00:49:58,948
Come over here.

1481
00:49:58,949 --> 00:50:01,689
He just goosed me. Then why couldn't I hear the bells?

1482
00:50:02,219 --> 00:50:04,029
- Why can't I hear the bells?
- Where is he?

1483
00:50:04,589 --> 00:50:05,958
He goosed me really hard.

1484
00:50:05,959 --> 00:50:07,228
I can't find Jong Min.

1485
00:50:07,229 --> 00:50:09,098
(Jong Min stays silent.)

1486
00:50:09,099 --> 00:50:11,229
Guys, keep it down and listen closely.

1487
00:50:13,239 --> 00:50:14,669
Jong Min, make a noise for us.

1488
00:50:16,309 --> 00:50:17,639
Oh, I found him.

1489
00:50:20,039 --> 00:50:21,239
- Hey!
- You should catch him.

1490
00:50:22,509 --> 00:50:23,509
Come over here.

1491
00:50:23,510 --> 00:50:24,548
Oh, I found him.

1492
00:50:24,549 --> 00:50:27,249
(Bull's-eye)

1493
00:50:28,719 --> 00:50:30,188
- Come over here.
- Did you catch him?

1494
00:50:30,189 --> 00:50:31,748
- Who is this?
- Did you catch him?

1495
00:50:31,749 --> 00:50:32,889
- Where is he?
- It's me.

1496
00:50:33,719 --> 00:50:34,759
- Who is this?
- It's me.

1497
00:50:35,119 --> 00:50:36,588
- Did you catch him?
- Who is this?

1498
00:50:36,589 --> 00:50:37,788
(He still survived.)

1499
00:50:37,789 --> 00:50:38,928
Stay still.

1500
00:50:38,929 --> 00:50:40,259
I won't let him slide.

1501
00:50:41,129 --> 00:50:42,169
Stay still and quiet down.

1502
00:50:43,829 --> 00:50:44,868
(He hit the target again.)

1503
00:50:44,869 --> 00:50:46,268
- Where is he?
- Who is this?

1504
00:50:46,269 --> 00:50:47,369
Where is he?

1505
00:50:47,499 --> 00:50:48,699
Why can't I hear the bells?

1506
00:50:48,869 --> 00:50:50,009
Where is he?

1507
00:50:50,069 --> 00:50:53,508
(Jong Min counterattacks with his secret weapon, goosing Se Yoon.)

1508
00:50:53,509 --> 00:50:54,738
I bet your finger hurts.

1509
