00:59:52,679 --> 00:59:54,148
What do you think of today's game?

1768
00:59:54,149 --> 00:59:55,919
Do you think you got back at DinDin?

1769
00:59:56,079 --> 00:59:57,889
You know life...

1770
00:59:58,249 --> 01:00:00,419
This is the best life.

1771
01:00:00,919 --> 01:00:02,889
See? We ended up in a nice place.

1772
01:00:03,159 --> 01:00:04,358
The last part of life has to be nice.

1773
01:00:04,359 --> 01:00:06,388
- It's all about the game twists.
- Right.

1774
01:00:06,389 --> 01:00:08,299
They must be cold outside tonight.

1775
01:00:09,699 --> 01:00:10,939
It will be really cold outside.

1776
01:00:11,269 --> 01:00:12,598
We are in Gangwon Province.

1777
01:00:12,599 --> 01:00:13,868
Right, it's cold here.

1778
01:00:13,869 --> 01:00:14,938
(Are they worrying or mocking?)

1779
01:00:14,939 --> 01:00:16,169
Good job, everyone.

1780
01:00:17,469 --> 01:00:18,538
Goodness.

1781
01:00:18,539 --> 01:00:20,908
(What's happening on the bunker bed in this windy Gangwon Province?)

1782
01:00:20,909 --> 01:00:22,009
Are you okay?

1783
01:00:22,239 --> 01:00:23,748
It's all right.

1784
01:00:23,749 --> 01:00:25,078
It's better than I thought.

1785
01:00:25,079 --> 01:00:26,609
Right, I just need to cover my face.

1786
01:00:26,979 --> 01:00:29,379
We still get to sleep on the bed.

1787
01:00:30,189 --> 01:00:31,419
I know, it's fine.

1788
01:00:31,649 --> 01:00:34,319
There's no cold rising from the floor.

1789
01:00:34,689 --> 01:00:36,559
- Right.
- That's the nice part.

1790
01:00:37,089 --> 01:00:40,299
You wouldn't end up here if you teamed up with me today.

1791
01:00:41,529 --> 01:00:44,049
If I had stayed with you, would I have won rock-paper-scissors?

1792
01:00:44,799 --> 01:00:46,069
Of course, for sure.

1793
01:00:46,599 --> 01:00:47,599
You think so?

1794
01:00:48,039 --> 01:00:50,538
I was so lonely today.

1795
01:00:50,539 --> 01:00:51,609
I played it all by myself.

1796
01:00:52,309 --> 01:00:54,009
It felt like I was ganged up.

1797
01:00:54,709 --> 01:00:55,839
Well,

1798
01:00:57,079 --> 01:00:58,379
I'm still jealous of you.

1799
01:00:58,479 --> 01:01:00,149
This episode is all about you.

1800
01:01:01,419 --> 01:01:03,549
It was my episode, but I felt so lonely.

1801
01:01:04,449 --> 01:01:06,649
I want to feel lonely and have an episode all about me.

1802
01:01:08,489 --> 01:01:10,328
There was an episode with six Jong Mins.

1803
01:01:10,329 --> 01:01:11,389
Yes.

1804
01:01:11,589 --> 01:01:13,559
I don't have an episode like that yet.

1805
01:01:13,999 --> 01:01:15,759
- The challenges.
- What?

1806
01:01:15,929 --> 01:01:17,029
Do more challenges.

1807
01:01:17,799 --> 01:01:19,959
They could make an episode like Lee Joon's Challenges.

1808
01:01:20,869 --> 01:01:22,138
You could be doing challenges all day long.

1809
01:01:22,139 --> 01:01:23,368
(A nonstop 24-hour challenge inferno)

1810
01:01:23,369 --> 01:01:25,168
- A challenge inferno.
- A challenge inferno.

1811
01:01:25,169 --> 01:01:26,539
I would be doing them all.

1812
01:01:27,709 --> 01:01:30,608
That would be the worst.

1813
01:01:30,609 --> 01:01:32,325
(The challenge episode already feels like it won't be easy.)

1814
01:01:32,349 --> 01:01:33,949
- Joon.
- Yes?

1815
01:01:34,049 --> 01:01:35,049
Look at the stars.

1816
01:01:37,219 --> 01:01:38,848
The stars. It's crazy.

1817
01:01:38,849 --> 01:01:41,118
In Gangwon Province, places like Yanggu...

1818
01:01:41,119 --> 01:01:44,028
and Cheorwon have clean air, so you can see many stars.

1819
01:01:44,029 --> 01:01:45,189
The stars look nice.

1820
01:01:45,959 --> 01:01:47,029
Goodnight.

1821
01:01:47,329 --> 01:01:48,428
Goodnight.

1822
01:01:48,429 --> 01:01:51,669
(Dear stars, please let me have my own special episode!)

1823
01:01:51,799 --> 01:01:54,969
(He endured Yanggu's cold night with his passionate dream.)

1824
01:01:56,169 --> 01:01:58,569
(The round sun rose brightly.)

1825
01:01:58,609 --> 01:02:00,579
Wake up!

1826
01:02:02,409 --> 01:02:04,608
(A bright voice...)

1827
01:02:04,609 --> 01:02:06,549
(suddenly rings out.)

1828
01:02:07,119 --> 01:02:10,289
(What was that?)

1829
01:02:10,889 --> 01:02:12,319
- Hello.
- What?

1830
01:02:13,459 --> 01:02:15,419
(He quickly covers his face.)

1831
01:02:15,559 --> 01:02:17,329
What's this?

1832
01:02:17,989 --> 01:02:19,558
Wake up!

1833
01:02:19,559 --> 01:02:20,221
(Who has this clear and pure voice?)

1834
01:02:20,231 --> 01:02:22,785
(Instead of the wake-up song, someone else wakes up the members.)

1835
01:02:22,809 --> 01:02:24,649
(Who are those girls?)

1836
01:02:25,009 --> 01:02:26,549
Wake up!

1837
01:02:27,749 --> 01:02:28,788
What is this?

1838
01:02:28,789 --> 01:02:30,819
(Who are the girls...)

1839
01:02:31,289 --> 01:02:33,289
(that surprised the members?)

1840
01:02:36,189 --> 01:02:37,228
What is this?

1841
01:02:37,229 --> 01:02:39,699
(ILLIT?)

1842
01:02:40,159 --> 01:02:45,799
(What's going on?)

1843
01:02:46,699 --> 01:02:50,669
(They came to 2 Days 1 Night as morning angels.)

1844
01:02:51,069 --> 01:02:54,539
(With their dreamy, kitschy ILLIT-core concept, )

1845
01:02:54,609 --> 01:02:56,348
(they became the first K-pop group to enter the Billboard chart...)

1846
01:02:56,349 --> 01:02:58,009
(with a debut song.)

1847
01:02:58,209 --> 01:03:01,249
(Global star ILLIT)

1848
01:03:02,649 --> 01:03:05,049
(They came to 2 Days 1 Night with their new song "It's Me.")

1849
01:03:08,619 --> 01:03:10,959
I guess it's their new song!

1850
01:03:13,399 --> 01:03:14,399
(Powerful)

1851
01:03:14,959 --> 01:03:19,599
(Even in the dust, the global stars' sharp choreography never falters.)

1852
01:03:21,669 --> 01:03:23,769
(ILLIT)

1853
01:03:24,309 --> 01:03:26,239
(They cheer without even knowing why.)

1854
01:03:26,479 --> 01:03:28,039
- What is this?
- ILLIT is here?

1855
01:03:28,339 --> 01:03:29,448
It's ILLIT.

1856
01:03:29,449 --> 01:03:30,508
Let's go to them.

1857
01:03:30,509 --> 01:03:32,548
- Hello.
- Hello!

1858
01:03:32,549 --> 01:03:35,249
- We haven't even washed up yet.
- We just woke up.

1859
01:03:35,279 --> 01:03:36,548
We smell!

1860
01:03:36,549 --> 01:03:38,888
- What kind of meeting is this?
- I can't go near them!

1861
01:03:38,889 --> 01:03:40,758
We invited such special guests.

1862
01:03:40,759 --> 01:03:42,558
Quickly get ready and come back.

1863
01:03:42,559 --> 01:03:43,958
Our breath smells, so we're going to wash up first.

1864
01:03:43,959 --> 01:03:45,029
Okay.

1865
01:03:45,729 --> 01:03:47,828
We just got up. I'm sorry.

1866
01:03:47,829 --> 01:03:49,428
We should go now.

1867
01:03:49,429 --> 01:03:51,299
- See you.
- What is this?

1868
01:03:51,799 --> 01:03:53,868
(The girls are left there all by themselves.)

1869
01:03:53,869 --> 01:03:54,898
Do you need some water?

1870
01:03:54,899 --> 01:03:55,969
Yes!

1871
01:03:56,469 --> 01:03:58,539
- Water!
- This is funny.

1872
01:04:00,579 --> 01:04:02,708
What kind of situation is this?

1873
01:04:02,709 --> 01:04:03,925
(They also find the situation funny.)

1874
01:04:03,949 --> 01:04:06,479
- There are so many cameras.
- Right.

1875
01:04:06,619 --> 01:04:07,678
I think it has the most cameras...

1876
01:04:07,679 --> 01:04:09,239
out of all the variety shows I've seen.

1877
01:04:09,519 --> 01:04:10,789
There are so many cameras.

1878
01:04:11,249 --> 01:04:13,389
What is this? Is this lotion?

1879
01:04:15,059 --> 01:04:17,688
(They normally don't even wash up in the morning.)

1880
01:04:17,689 --> 01:04:19,929
ILLIT is here. It's ILLIT.

1881
01:04:20,729 --> 01:04:22,329
I should look pretty.

1882
01:04:22,829 --> 01:04:24,068
ILLIT is here.

1883
01:04:24,069 --> 01:04:25,405
(They're making such a fuss because guests are here.)

1884
01:04:25,429 --> 01:04:28,639
Since we have a girl group here, I should go with a hip-hop style.

1885
01:04:29,339 --> 01:04:31,569
Do I look dressed up? I do, right?

1886
01:04:32,739 --> 01:04:34,808
- Hello.
- Hello.

1887
01:04:34,809 --> 01:04:36,379
- Welcome.
- To see them here...

1888
01:04:36,449 --> 01:04:37,748
(They finally approach with confidence.)

1889
01:04:37,749 --> 01:04:39,018
Why did they come so far?

1890
01:04:39,019 --> 01:04:41,118
- Right.
- Right. They came so far.

1891
01:04:41,119 --> 01:04:42,919
- Hello.
- Hello.

1892
01:04:43,089 --> 01:04:45,348
- Do you know them?
- Are you close with them?

1893
01:04:45,349 --> 01:04:47,118
- From "Amazing Saturday."
- I met him many times.

1894
01:04:47,119 --> 01:04:48,318
- "Amazing Saturday."
- Really?

1895
01:04:48,319 --> 01:04:49,988
She's basically a regular member on "Amazing Saturday."

1896
01:04:49,989 --> 01:04:51,028
(They met often on Saturdays.)

1897
01:04:51,029 --> 01:04:52,528
Did DinDin go home?

1898
01:04:52,529 --> 01:04:53,899
He's getting dressed up.

1899
01:04:54,259 --> 01:04:56,168
DinDin is busy getting all dolled up.

1900
01:04:56,169 --> 01:04:58,298
ILLIT is here. Please give them a hand.

1901
01:04:58,299 --> 01:04:59,568
Right!

1902
01:04:59,569 --> 01:05:01,338
- Are we proceeding without DinDin?
- Yes.

1903
01:05:01,339 --> 01:05:03,008
- Without DinDin?
- We don't need him.

1904
01:05:03,009 --> 01:05:04,438
- He doesn't matter.
- Right.

1905
01:05:04,439 --> 01:05:05,978
It's perfectly 4 versus 4 as well.

1906
01:05:05,979 --> 01:05:07,478
- Right.
- It's perfect for a game.

1907
01:05:07,479 --> 01:05:08,678
- We could play.
- Yes.

1908
01:05:08,679 --> 01:05:11,308
It's really nice, but we came really far.

1909
01:05:11,309 --> 01:05:13,218
Coming to 2 Days 1 Night would be nice,

1910
01:05:13,219 --> 01:05:14,248
but it wouldn't be great...

1911
01:05:14,249 --> 01:05:15,478
- to come here early in the morning.
- That's right.

1912
01:05:15,479 --> 01:05:16,818
I was so excited on my way here.

1913
01:05:16,819 --> 01:05:18,218
After seeing the beds...

1914
01:05:18,219 --> 01:05:19,658
- in the middle of the playground, - That's right.

1915
01:05:19,659 --> 01:05:21,858
- we all got excited.
- Why?

1916
01:05:21,859 --> 01:05:24,058
- At the thought that we would be...
- To think there are people there.

1917
01:05:24,059 --> 01:05:26,599
Waking up the people in those beds...

1918
01:05:26,759 --> 01:05:27,858
It would have been your first time seeing people sleep...

1919
01:05:27,859 --> 01:05:28,928
in the playground.

1920
01:05:28,929 --> 01:05:30,475
- Right. It was the first time.
- It was the first time.

1921
01:05:30,499 --> 01:05:32,698
When we first debuted,

1922
01:05:32,699 --> 01:05:35,938
we once appeared on 2 Days 1 Night.

1923
01:05:35,939 --> 01:05:36,969
Really?

1924
01:05:37,469 --> 01:05:38,708
- That's right!
- Right!

1925
01:05:38,709 --> 01:05:40,108
- On the music show?
- That's right.

1926
01:05:40,109 --> 01:05:41,338
- That's right.
- Yes.

1927
01:05:41,339 --> 01:05:42,748
That's right!

1928
01:05:42,749 --> 01:05:44,525
(They made a brief appearance just 3 days after their debut.)

1929
01:05:44,549 --> 01:05:46,229
- That's right.
- You've already become...

1930
01:05:46,449 --> 01:05:47,718
such huge stars.

1931
01:05:47,719 --> 01:05:49,095
(They've grown in to major stars since they last saw them.)

1932
01:05:49,119 --> 01:05:51,319
Wonhee looks taller than DinDin.

1933
01:05:51,389 --> 01:05:52,418
Hey.

1934
01:05:52,419 --> 01:05:53,989
That's true.

1935
01:05:54,019 --> 01:05:55,019
- Hold on.
- What are you saying?

1936
01:05:55,020 --> 01:05:56,288
How tall are you, Wonhee?

1937
01:05:56,289 --> 01:05:58,088
- She's tall.
- Hey.

1938
01:05:58,089 --> 01:05:59,128
It's hard to tell.

1939
01:05:59,129 --> 01:06:00,898
She wore low-heeled shoes.

1940
01:06:00,899 --> 01:06:02,058
The heels are a bit low today.

1941
01:06:02,059 --> 01:06:03,498
Mine are lower.

1942
01:06:03,499 --> 01:06:04,669
Mine are lower.

1943
01:06:05,129 --> 01:06:07,138
You should greet her since she's here.

1944
01:06:07,139 --> 01:06:08,199
Go next to her.

1945
01:06:08,339 --> 01:06:10,368
Just walk past her.

1946
01:06:10,369 --> 01:06:11,508
(Just walk past her with your back straight.)

1947
01:06:11,509 --> 01:06:12,808
- Just walk past her.
- Hold on.

1948
01:06:12,809 --> 01:06:14,339
Could you put some volume to my hair?

1949
01:06:14,439 --> 01:06:15,439
(Quickly adding some volume)

1950
01:06:15,440 --> 01:06:17,049
- She wants more volume.
- Okay.

1951
01:06:17,079 --> 01:06:18,978
- Just walk past each other.
- Okay.

1952
01:06:18,979 --> 01:06:20,049
Just walk past each other.

1953
01:06:21,149 --> 01:06:22,649
They're both...

1954
01:06:24,689 --> 01:06:26,258
(They're about the same height.)

1955
01:06:26,259 --> 01:06:27,419
It's hard to tell.

1956
01:06:27,889 --> 01:06:29,158
(He's flustered.)

1957
01:06:29,159 --> 01:06:30,558
- I think Wonhee is taller.
- Hello.

1958
01:06:30,559 --> 01:06:32,798
Don't you tell people you're 170cm tall?

1959
01:06:32,799 --> 01:06:34,358
I'm 162cm tall.

1960
01:06:34,359 --> 01:06:35,698
You're only 162cm tall?

1961
01:06:35,699 --> 01:06:37,599
What are you saying?

1962
01:06:37,729 --> 01:06:39,099
- You're 162cm tall?
- Yes.

1963
01:06:39,339 --> 01:06:40,639
I'm not wearing any shoe lifts.

1964
01:06:40,839 --> 01:06:42,139
No.

1965
01:06:42,239 --> 01:06:44,868
(Quickly moving back)

1966
01:06:44,869 --> 01:06:46,338
I think you've gotten shorter.

1967
01:06:46,339 --> 01:06:47,638
I think she grew taller.

1968
01:06:47,639 --> 01:06:48,738
Right. She looks tall.

1969
01:06:48,739 --> 01:06:49,878
Measure your height again. You've grown.

1970
01:06:49,879 --> 01:06:51,749
- You're 162cm tall?
- How tall are you?

1971
01:06:52,009 --> 01:06:53,618
- What?
- How tall are you?

1972
01:06:53,619 --> 01:06:54,679
How tall are you?

1973
01:06:55,049 --> 01:06:56,249
Why?

1974
01:06:57,389 --> 01:06:58,818
What's wrong with being short?

1975
01:06:58,819 --> 01:07:00,258
- Right.
- Yes.

1976
01:07:00,259 --> 01:07:01,319
What are we doing today?

1977
01:07:02,559 --> 01:07:04,558
Let's let it slide just this once.

1978
01:07:04,559 --> 01:07:07,428
ILLIT, our special guests...

1979
01:07:07,429 --> 01:07:08,528
said that they wanted...

1980
01:07:08,529 --> 01:07:10,598
- to experience 2 Days 1 Night.
- Yes.

1981
01:07:10,599 --> 01:07:12,398
We're going to do the morning mission together.

1982
01:07:12,399 --> 01:07:14,198
- Okay.
- That's so nice.

1983
01:07:14,199 --> 01:07:17,269
We're going to do the Art and PE Performance Exam...

1984
01:07:17,539 --> 01:07:19,578
to get a special prize.

1985
01:07:19,579 --> 01:07:20,679
Art and PE.

1986
01:07:21,179 --> 01:07:22,278
- A prize?
- A prize?

1987
01:07:22,279 --> 01:07:23,409
- Arts and PE?
- What is it?

1988
01:07:23,509 --> 01:07:26,478
You'll split into teams of 4 and 5...

1989
01:07:26,479 --> 01:07:29,249
and compete three rounds.

1990
01:07:29,419 --> 01:07:30,588
For the winning team...

1991
01:07:30,589 --> 01:07:33,359
Gangwon Province is famous for its beef.

1992
01:07:33,789 --> 01:07:36,659
The winning team will receive a set of grade two plus Korean beef...

1993
01:07:36,929 --> 01:07:39,098
we bought from Gangwon Province.

1994
01:07:39,099 --> 01:07:40,598
We really have to win this.

1995
01:07:40,599 --> 01:07:42,929
- You have to take this.
- We should.

1996
01:07:44,169 --> 01:07:46,068
Wait! It'll go bad if you put it here.

1997
01:07:46,069 --> 01:07:47,938
- That's right.
- That's right.

1998
01:07:47,939 --> 01:07:49,108
(Protecting the beef with her whole body)

1999
01:07:49,109 --> 01:07:51,368
You're not acting like yesterday!

2000
01:07:51,369 --> 01:07:52,785
(He's furious at Team Preparation's unusual behavior.)

2001
01:07:52,809 --> 01:07:55,078
- There's sunlight here.
- That's right. It will go bad.

2002
01:07:55,079 --> 01:07:56,479
Let us at least briefly see it.

2003
01:07:57,679 --> 01:07:58,708
(Today's prize, grade two plus Korean beef set)

2004
01:07:58,709 --> 01:07:59,878
- This looks expensive.
- Look at the color.

2005
01:07:59,879 --> 01:08:02,549
- Chuck flap tail, sirloin...
- Chuck flat tail and sirloin...

2006
01:08:02,589 --> 01:08:04,388
- Doesn't it have a great color?
- It's amazing.

2007
01:08:04,389 --> 01:08:05,758
It has a great color, right? Doesn't it look delicious?

2008
01:08:05,759 --> 01:08:06,759
- Yes.
- Yes.

2009
01:08:06,760 --> 01:08:08,395
- Look at this!
- It's got a lot of meat.

2010
01:08:08,419 --> 01:08:10,299
- They should take it back now.
- I don't know.

2011
01:08:10,859 --> 01:08:12,699
- It's from...
- Please put it in the fridge.

2012
01:08:13,029 --> 01:08:15,928
You should split into teams first, right?

2013
01:08:15,929 --> 01:08:17,928
- Yes.
- The ILLIT members...

2014
01:08:17,929 --> 01:08:20,298
can choose who they want to team up with.

2015
01:08:20,299 --> 01:08:21,375
(Each person chooses the teammate they want.)

2016
01:08:21,399 --> 01:08:24,169
In ILLIT, Yunah and Minju will be on the same team.

2017
01:08:24,969 --> 01:08:26,739
- The big sisters.
- The big sisters.

2018
01:08:26,979 --> 01:08:28,308
- They're the big sisters.
- The big sisters.

2019
01:08:28,309 --> 01:08:30,748
Then the little sisters will be on the same team.

2020
01:08:30,749 --> 01:08:32,348
In the end,

2021
01:08:32,349 --> 01:08:33,778
there will be one person left.

2022
01:08:33,779 --> 01:08:34,779
